title: microwaved oven fried potatoes
directions: Melt butter in oven 45 seconds on High.
Slice potatoes and onion in alternating layers, adding salt and pepper as desired. Stir butter into vegetables after each layer to be sure they are coated.
Cook on High 15 minutes, stirring after each 5 minutes.

title: fiesta onions
directions: Slice onions and soak 3 hours in this brine.
Stir often. Drain thoroughly.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery seed, salt and pepper.
This makes a great salad.
Keeps well.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, seasoning mix and green chilies.
Cook on low for 25 minutes, covered. Spoon a little into bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan.
Then, layer tortillas, breaking them to fit.
Cover with sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat, making 2 layers.
Bake 1/2 hour or so at 325°. Freezes well.

title: fried pies
directions: Put fruit and water in meduim sized heavey sauce pan and let stand for 1 hour or overnight.
Cook covered over low heat until thick enough to cling to spoon about 45 minutes.
Stir in sugar.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Slice rolls.
Spread mixture on inside of roll; saving some mixture for tops.
Place equal portions of ham and cheese in rolls.
Place top on roll and spread remaining mixture over sandwiches.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn in 1/4 cup of oil.
Be careful not to burn.
When you are through popping corn, pick out all unpopped kernels (this takes a little time, but it's worth it).
Put corn in a very large pot or bowl.
In a medium pot, combine water, sugar and 3 or 4 drops of food coloring.
Boil this until the sugar is dissolved. Add vinegar; cook until it comes to a hard boil (250°).
Very carefully pour mixture, little by little, over popcorn, stirring often.
Let cool, then break up.

title: stuffing chicken casserole
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions and spread over the chicken mixture.
(If you use a deep casserole, you can alternate chicken, stuffing, chicken, stuffing.)
Pour chicken broth on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: wake-up casserole
directions: Place croutons in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Top with cheese and mushrooms. Brown sausage and onion. Drain and spread over cheese. Beat eggs with 2 cups milk and seasonings. Pour over sausage. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Mix soup with 1/2 cup milk and spread on top of casserole before baking. Bake in a 325° oven for 60 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onions until pink color is gone.
Stir in mushroom and chicken soup, enchilada sauce, green chili peppers and milk.
May freeze part of sauce to use later or make large casserole.
Will make 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Use alternate layers of Doritos chips, sauce and grated or sliced Velveeta cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: smoky barbecue brisket
directions: Place brisket in a large shallow roasting pan.
Pour Liquid Smoke and Worcestershire sauce over brisket.
Sprinkle evenly with onion powder, garlic powder, summer savory, salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: Brown and then drain the ground beef and simmer for 45 minutes in 7 cups water, then add remaining ingredients and simmer for 3 hours or in large pressure pot for 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and cream of tartar together.
Set aside. Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and vanilla. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture in four parts, beating after each addition.
Shape into balls from 1 teaspoon of batter.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Store in covered container to keep fresh.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour in a saucepan. Add egg yolks and gradually add milk, stirring until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until filling boils. Remove from heat; blend in margarine and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and extract; beat well. Combine dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide in half.
Cover.
Chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll each half to 1/8-inch thickness for thin cookies or 1/4-inch thickness for thicker cookies.
Cut into shapes with cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets 7 to 8 minutes for thin cookies in a 375° oven, or 10 to 12 minutes for thick cookies.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen thin cookies or 3 dozen thick cookies.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan on low heat or in microwave. Remove from heat and let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Place in a pan or on cookie sheet Hershey bars, broken in bits, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Set aside.
In another pan mix sugar, milk, butter and salt together.
After mixture starts to simmer, cook 5 minutes over low heat; stir often.
Pour over chocolate mixture and stir until everything is melted.
Add nuts last.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet, spread evenly and let cool. Cut into desired size pieces and store in airtight containers. Makes 4 1/2 pounds.

title: missouri corn pudding
directions: Whip together in baking dish all ingredients except corn. When well mixed, stir in the corn.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until mixture is set.

title: jellied pigs feet
directions: Wash feet and shanks, put in large kettle and cover with water, bring to boiling point and skim.
Add garlic, onion, peppercorns and bay leaf and simmer for about 4 hours or until meat leaves the bone.
Cool.
Remove bones, fat and skin.
Return meat to liquid, add salt and vinegar and pour into loaf or tube pan.
Set in refrigerator overnight or until firm.
Remove fat from top before serving.
Additional vinegar or lemon may be used.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Make a custard of the egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup water and dissolve in hot custard as it is removed from stove.
Chill and, when mixture is just about set, fold in Cool Whip.
Return to fridge.

title: yogurt crescent rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes, stir in yogurt mixture, egg and egg white.
Stir 2 cups flour and salt mixture into yogurt mixture.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, sweet pepper and onion together. Pour sugar over mixture.
Boil mustard, oil and vinegar for 2 minutes, then add to mixture. Let set in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: no-work meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape in loaf in a shallow baking pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: company cornbread
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Pour into hot iron skillet with 2 to 3 tablespoons hot oil covering bottom of skillet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dill dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix, chill and serve with veggies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, vegetables, cheese and seasonings. Toss to mix.
Fold in Miracle Whip and mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Chop cucumbers and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain and chop everything and put in jar with vinegar and sugar. Put in jar and store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and chill until partially set.
Add cranberries and apples to mixture.
Add grapes and nuts.
Pour in mold or pan and chill until set.

title: caribbean cooler punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 quart pitcher.
Serve chilled or over ice.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: hamburger zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain and add salt, pepper, oregano, tomato sauce and cheese.
Cook until cheese starts to melt.
Slice zucchini into bottom of casserole until well covered. Pour ground beef mixture over top of zucchini; top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: veggie bars
directions: Pat rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Be sure seams are sealed.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, and dressing mix.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on top and pat gently into cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant 1/4 inch thick, peel.
Soak in salt water for 30 minutes (about 2 tablespoons salt in large bowl).
Put a saucer on top to immerse eggplant in water.
Brown ground beef, when almost done add green pepper and onion.
Season with seasoned salt, when pepper and onion are done drain meat mixture.
Add tomatoes and heat meat mixture.
Drain eggplant, fry in hot oil until brown. Drain, put a little meat mixture in bottom of casserole.
Add layer of eggplant, a layer of meat mixture, 1/4 cup bread crumbs, 1/4 cup Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Cheddar.
Layer eggplant, meat, bread crumbs and cheeses until all is used.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: swedish pecans
directions: Toast pecans in oven at 325° for 10 to 20 minutes or until light brown, stirring occasionally.
Fold sugar and salt into egg whites.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold nuts into beaten egg whites.
Place melted butter in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until nuts are coated and no butter remains in pan.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool and break apart.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine in saucepan, milk, sugar and margarine.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir and pour into buttered loaf pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Cut and serve.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saut vegetables in butter until tender. Add flour, milk, egg yolks, pepper, crabmeat and half of the cheese. Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: colored noodle jewelry
directions: Mix rubbing alcohol and food coloring in plastic food container.
Mix well.
Add pasta and stir.
Remove pasta.
Dry on wax paper for 1 hour.
String colored pasta onto elastic to make necklaces or bracelets.
Can also be glued onto paper for pictures.

title: ruth's sugar cookies delight
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill dough.
Form in balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet; flatten with a glass or a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add oatmeal and sugar.
Blend butter into dry ingredients with dough blender until crumbly. Press 1/2 mixture into square glass pan or glass pie plate.
Put rhubarb on top and then remaining crumbs.
Put in microwave and bake on High for 12 minutes.

title: lazy boy cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add other ingredients and mix. Form into small balls. Set aside. Melt half a bar of paraffin wax. Add 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate morsels. Drop balls into mixture and put on wax paper.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt and add milk slowly.
Stir until thickened.
Add potatoes and heat until boils.
Pour into shallow pan and bake at 350°.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over top and bake until done.

title: creamy turkey and pasta primavera
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare mostaccioli according to package directions.
Add broccoli, carrots, green onions and red pepper the last 5 minutes of cooking time; drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add mostaccioli, vegetable mixture and turkey. Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.

title: skillet beef and noodles for the masses(18 gallons at 6-ounce per serving)
directions: (Just the thing to make when you are expecting 384 people over for supper!)
Kettle fry beef, onions, green peppers, chili powder, garlic and salt until meat is done.
Combine noodles and beef gravy with meat and mix well.
If thin, thicken and cook until clear.

title: potato chip chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Fill a large sealable plastic bag with potato chips. Crush them.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Pour uncooked rice (except seasonings) in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour in one cup of water and stir.
Lay uncooked, salted and peppered chicken pieces on rice.
Pour combined soups over chicken.
Pour seasonings from rice box over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
So easy and so good.

title: old-fashioned apple crunch(diabetic)
directions: Mix the oats, 1/2 cup flour, cinnamon and margarine until crumbly in texture.
Place 1/2 of mixture in the bottom of the baking pan.
Combine the apples, 1 tablespoon of flour, cinnamon, juice and sweetener.
Spread over the oat mixture.
Cover with the remainder of the oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cherry pie
directions: Mix together tapioca, sugar, butter and cherries.
Let stand until you make your shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Place the tomatoes over the fire to cook gently for ten minutes.
Then add sugar, salt, pepper and butter.
Cook ten minutes longer.
Stir in the bread crumbs.

title: parmesan knots
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine oil, cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic powder and pepper. Set aside. Cut each biscuit in half. Roll each portion into a 6-inch rope; tie in a loose knot. Place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 450° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately brush with the Parmesan mixture, then brush again. Serve warm or freeze for up to 2 months.

title: english cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water and cool.
Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt and raisin juice.
Sift together and add flour, soda and baking powder.
Add cooked raisins and nut meats.
Spread on a greased 12 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put a light powdered sugar icing over cookies after baking.
Cut in squares.
You may substitute chocolate or butterscotch morsels in place of nuts.

title: layered veggie casserole
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs
and pour margarine over all.
Bake at 350°
40 to 45 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine.
Add meat, onion and garlic. Cook until meat changes color and begins to brown slightly.
Stir in flour.
Then add soup, mushrooms, salt, pepper and paprika. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat to serving temperature.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat flour, baking soda, salt and bananas.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Heat oil in a large ovenproof skillet or casserole dish. Saute potatoes, garlic and seasonings together for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Cook pineapple and 1 cup sugar on low heat until sugar melts. Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar real good.
Add salt and vanilla to cheese mixture.
Beat eggs until stiff.
Add to cheese mixture.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Pour pineapple and sugar into pie shell.
Pour cream cheese mixture onto this.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 35 minutes longer.
If nuts seem to be getting too brown, put brown paper bag over top of pie.

title: mayfair salad dressing
directions: Peel and slice garlic, celery and onion.
Put everything except eggs and oil into a blender.
Blend for a few seconds.
Add the eggs and blend for a few seconds.
Add the eggs and blend for a few more seconds.
Add the oil, one quarter at a time, blending between each addition.
Then blend a few more seconds after all the oil has been added.
Makes 1 quart.
May be refrigerated for up to 2 weeks.

title: corn bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can add onion and pepper, if desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour in a pan. Dabble butter on top. Bake at 325° for an hour or until kind of crispy on top.

title: potato-spam casserole
directions: Bake all together in casserole dish until bubbly and golden brown at 350°.

title: believe it or not cookie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Spread with fork. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: housewarming potatoes
directions: Boil and cook potatoes.
Grate and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dot with butter and cheese.

title: bubble bread
directions: Use only yeast bread dough.
(Frozen bread dough works well.)

title: tomato supreme
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes and remove pulp, leaving a shell. Combine remaining ingredients and fill tomato shells with mixture. Chill and serve.
Garnish with lettuce leaves and carrot sticks if you like.

title: breaded chicken breasts
directions: In a bowl beat eggs.
Place the bread crumbs in a flat dish. Dip split chicken breasts in eggs and place in bread crumbs on both sides.
You can remove the chicken skins if desired before dipping into eggs.
In frying long pan, put vegetable oil and place chickens in pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Thaw
oysters,	if
frozen.
Drain,
reserving	liquid. Remove any shell particles.
Saute
onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add
oyster
liquid,
half and half, potatoes, corn, salt and
pepper.
Heat,
stirring
occasionally. Add oysters and heat for
3 to 5 minutes longer or until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Do
not let chowder boil.
Garnish with chopped parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Melt margarine; mix with cracker crumbs.
Drain oysters through strainer; save juice.
Wash oysters.
Layer 1/3 crumbs in baking dish, then 1/3 oysters; alternate until all used but a few cracker crumbs.
Before using the last crackers, mix cream, juice and sauce together and pour over oysters.
Add rest of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mary anne's banana punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze.
Thaw to a slush and just before serving add 7-Up.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Break lettuce in bowl.
Place mandarin oranges on top of lettuce.
Sprinkle top with red onion rings and sliced almonds that have been lightly browned with butter and then cooled.

title: grandma gaither's banana nut cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; add soda and buttermilk and vanilla; add flour and continue beating for 4 minutes.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into a tube pan, bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blender cole slaw
directions: Place cabbage in blender; drain. In a medium-sized bowl, sprinkle with celery salt and add dressing. Mix well. Chill, tightly covered, in refrigerator. Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour over chicken mixture in casserole.
Pour remaining 2 cups of broth over this.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cider waldorf mold
directions: In a saucepan bring 1 cup of apple cider to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling cider, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining apple cider.
Chill until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Fold in chopped apples, celery and pecans. Pour into a 3-cup mold or into 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce-lined plates.
Serve with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the rest and beat until well blended with mixer.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Test with toothpick.

title: vegetable clam chowder(low-fat)
directions: In a large saucepan, cook all ingredients except clams, about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add clam juice and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add clams.
Has only about 3 grams fat.

title: angel bavarian
directions: Make
pudding
according to instructions on box.
Slice cake in	half
lengthwise.
Place
in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cooled pudding
over bottom of cake.
Put top piece of cake on pudding. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip.	Can sprinkle
chopped
nuts
on
top
of Cool Whip and coconut (optional).

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Pour 1/2 batter into a greased and floured 13x9 in pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 min. or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed on mixer.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well, stir in almond extract.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut with 2 1/4-inch round cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown. Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Cool.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash, quarter or cut squash into large, sliced pieces.
Do not remove the peel.
Place in a medium saucepan.
Cover with water. Cook until the squash is tender for about 15 to 20 minutes. (Squash can be cooked in 2 minutes in a pressure cooker.)
Drain water off thoroughly after squash has cooked, but save a small amount (1/4 cup) for later.
Mash the squash with a fork or potato masher.
Add salt, pepper, butter or margarine, diced onions and saved water.
Stir well.
Return this mixture to the stove on low heat and continue to cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: pie tree
directions: Spread the two pie crusts out on a cookie sheet, lined with aluminum foil. Cut each crust to the shape of a Christmas tree without cutting into the aluminum foil. Sprinkle the spices over the trees and press lightly into the dough with your fingers. Take small bits of the leftover dough and roll into small balls. Place the balls on the trees as you would hang Christmas ornaments. Press slightly into the dough to flatten the balls. Bake the trees at 425° until lightly browned. Cool. Decorate with cream cheese that has been tinted green and place the whole cloves to look like pine cones or branches. Sprinkle on some parsley. The dough that was placed as ornaments can be decorated with white or other colored cream cheese. Yellow cheese, rolled into balls, can be added as extra decorations. Serve with a knife nearby so guests can cut the trees into eating pieces.

title: swiss steak with mushrooms
directions: Combine flour and seasonings.
Dredge steak in seasoned flour. Brown steak thoroughly in hot oil; remove from pan.
In Dutch oven, combine soup, broth and water.
Bring to boil.
Add steak; pour mushrooms over meat.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: low-fat creamed chicken(for sandwiches)
directions: Drain chicken and place chunks in Corning Ware dish on stove. Break up chicken into small pieces (shred) while heating on medium-low.
When chicken is shredded, add soup, dill weed and salt and pepper to taste.
Continue cooking on medium-low to medium for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Allow to cool slightly and serve on buns.
Prep/Cook time:
15 minutes.
Easy.

title: snacking granola bars
directions: Toast oats in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place toasted oats in a large bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Press firmly into a well-greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, blend in sugar, add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture, alternately with bananas and liquid.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool several hours or overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine the juice of one lemon and the juice from a No. 2 can of pineapple chunks with 3/4 cup of sugar.
Boil together with 3 tablespoons cornstarch until it thickens in a double boiler. Remove from heat; grind the rind of 1 orange.
Cool and add these fruits:

1 (No. 2) can pineapple chunks, 1 (No. 2) can of pears (drained and diced on paper towel), 1 banana (sliced), 1 cup of whole seedless grapes, 1 cup of mandarin orange slices (drained) and 1 cup of nuts.
Chill.

title: scrumptious pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add oats.
Stir in mixture of egg and milk.
Blend in oil.
Bake on lightly greased griddle until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with any raw vegetables or chips.

title: orange cake
directions: Break eggs into bowl.
Beat until frothy.
Beat in sugar and melted butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour milk to first mixture.
Fold in raisins and oranges.
Pour in a greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch square) and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen berries.
Stir until berries are thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch flat bowl until firm.
Spread sour cream over.
Pour remaining jello mixture over and refrigerate until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; chop chestnuts into small pieces.
Put everything together in small mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer until blended.
Store in refrigerator 1 day before using. Good with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: grape salad
directions: Add red and green grapes to your liking and brown sugar to taste.
Mix together all ingredients well.
Brown raw almonds.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a boil for 1 minute the cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk. Add in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Stir until thick. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Let stand until dry.

title: mato* dumplins
directions: Pa likes his mato* dumplins sugared so this is how we fix 'em*, but ye* can put salt instead of sugar.
Anyways, bil* the matos* then pinch off dough and add to this.
Cook about 20 minutes or until hard.
Add sugar or salt to taste.

title: "hot" zucchini squash
directions: Boil zucchini for 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Place 1/2 of zucchini in greased casserole and sprinkle with cheese and crumbs. Top with remainder of zucchini.
Cover with tomatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turtle pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels with 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Spread evenly on bottom of prepared pastry shell.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in baking dish in order given.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: treasure-trove oatmeal pie(in honor of stallion, "matann")
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats, coconut, raisins and undrained pineapple.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350°
oven for 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool on rack. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with onion in boiling salted water.
Drain well. Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Melt butter or margarine, toss with stuffing mix.
Spread half the stuffing mixture in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: overnight raisin oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oatmeal and milk.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to cook, beat in eggs and margarine.
Stir in raisins.
Add dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
If batter seems too thick, add more milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, up to 3 tablespoons.
Cook on lightly greased griddle or frying pan.
Cook until a few bubbles appear on top.
Turn to brown other side. Serve with honey or syrup.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together salmon, soup, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and onion juice.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake in a loaf or casserole pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
Pour white sauce over salmon loaf and garnish with hard-boiled eggs.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat together thoroughly. Add corn.
Mix.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly. Cook in 350° oven about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: After shelling eggs and washing, halve the eggs.
Scoop out egg yolks into a bowl.
Then add 1 heaping tablespoonful of mayonnaise and 3/4 teaspoon of pickle relish to egg yolks.
Mix well.
If too dry, add a smidge of mayonnaise at a time.
Taste to test flavor. When the right consistency and flavor, scoop a bit into each egg half.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: champagne punch
directions: Add fruit juices and water.
Let that dilute in punch bowl, then mix.
Just prior to serving, add ice, champagne and ginger ale.
Scoop in raspberry sherbet.
Serve.
Serves approximately 25.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix on high:
flour, sugar, cinnamon, milk and eggs.
Stir apples into batter with spoon.
In a large skillet, heat approximately 1/2-inch oil (hot enough for deep frying).
Drop small ladles of fritter batter into hot oil (fritter should be about 2 1/2-inches in diameter).
When edges are golden brown, flip over.
Approximately 8 fritters may be frying at one time.
Drain on paper towels.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate. Run cold water over broccoli to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and onion.
Put in pie pan.
In a small bowl, place eggs, Bisquick, milk, salt and pepper. Beat 1 minute with mixer.
Pour in pie pan. Bake 25 to 35 minutes until inserted knife comes out clean. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pistolettes
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and drain. Cook rice and broccoli in separate dishes. Combine, in skillet, meat, rice, broccoli and cubed Velveeta cheese. Add cream of mushroom soup and salt and pepper to taste. Mix well. Let cheese melt. Take pistolette rolls and hollow out rolls and stuff with ingredients. Cook rolls as instructed on package.

title: pineapple-orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl 3 to 4 minutes. Grease and flour 3 cake pans. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce, stirring to break it up.
Chill until partially congealed.
Add bananas and nuts; stir.
Pour into pan; let set until firm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients with milk.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs until creamy and add milks one at a time.
Mix well after each and then add
sugar
and mix well.
After that add regular milk to fill freezer to full stage.

title: green chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease 10-inch pie pan or shallow casserole.
Line plate with split chiles, covering bottom of pan completely; extend up sides as much as possible.
Combine cheese, eggs, cream, onion, salt, garlic and pepper in blender about 2 minutes.
Carefully pour into pie plate and bake about 30 minutes.
Let cool slightly before cutting into wedges.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine soups, milk and butter in crock-pot or heavy kettle. Mix well and simmer.
Add crabmeat and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly. Serve piping hot with crackers or garlic toast.
May use fresh steamed shrimp or mock crabmeat.
Serves 6.

title: carly's taco salad
directions: Toss with small bottle of Thousand Island dressing.
Serve with a 1-pound bag of nacho cheese Doritos on side.

title: cheesy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and one egg, mixing until well blended.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.
Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and garnish with crushed nuts or Cool Whip.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add bananas.
Beat 2 minutes. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Turn into 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on cake rack.
Spread Creamy Nut Filling on layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
In separate bowl, mix baking soda, flour and salt. Combine butter mixture with flour mixture. Add vanilla.
Mix well.

Chill in covered bowl for at least 2 hours or overnight. Roll out a portion of dough on lightly floured waxed paper to 1/8-inch. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown. Remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Lay rice on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix onion soup and water in pan. Place chicken on top of that, then broccoli. Next, dilute cream of chicken soup with 1/2 cup water; pour over broccoli. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: almond biscotti(servings:  4)
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together cinnamon, baking powder, cloves and flour.
Add to first mixture along with the almonds.
Separate dough into 3 parts and roll each part into a rope.

Place on greased or oiled cookie sheet and flatten. Brush with mixture of egg yolk and water (you needn't use all). Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until center is slightly firm. Cool slightly on rack.
Slice diagonally with sharp knife.

title: stuffed shells
directions: In a 5-quart pan, fill 1/2 full of water; add salt.
When boiling, add shells.
Stir carefully, as to not break or tear shells.
Cook until tender.
Cool.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter and pour into bowl.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Add to onions and butter.
Season with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into unbaked pie shell or pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put into a greased 9 x 14-inch cake pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients and sprinkle over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue deer meat
directions: Soak venison in 1 can of beer, garlic buds, onion and bay leaves.
Soak 3 hours or more before cooking.
Then cut up meat. Mix sauce ingredients and pour sauce over and cook in crock-pot until tender.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Roll into walnut size balls and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Place in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients and heat until cheese melts.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In a very large bowl, mix cereal, sugar, flour, salt and baking soda.
Add well-beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well with electric mixer 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. (Store remaining batter in refrigerator.
Good up to 5 weeks.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown and cut chops.
Peel
and
slice potatoes.
Layer potatoes in
a
x
9-inch pan.
Cover this layer with pork chop pieces.
Mix
together
in
a
bowl
sour cream and soup. Pour over chops.
Bake
at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are
tender.
If onion is used, layer on top of chops and before pouring on the soup mixture.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put potatoes and onions in mixing bowl.
Add flour and seasoning, mixing well.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat until cheese is smooth and creamy. Slowly add sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip. Add lemon pudding (dry). Spoon into crust and chill.

title: old fashion meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, soak bread in milk 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix gently.
Shape into 8 x 5 x 1 1/2-inch loaf.
Place on rack in pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Microwave Directions:
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 7 to 9 1/2 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking.
Makes 4 cups.

title: krystie's favorite pancakes(no fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place 1/4 cup of milk on griddle.
Cook until golden.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar, salt, vinegar, pineapple juice and butter in double boiler until it thickens.
Cool.
Fold in cherries, marshmallows, pineapple and oranges, then fold in the whipped cream and chill.

title: bride and groom punch(makes 100 three ounce servings)
directions: Combine juices in large bowl.
Gradually add chilled wine and stir until dissolved.
Chill until serving time.
Just before serving time, add ice block and champagne.
Garnish with orange and lime slices.
For 12 servings, use 1/3 cup frozen juices, 1 (28 ounce) bottled wine and 1 bottle champagne.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender, saving broth.
Cool and dice chicken, then put into an oblong casserole dish.
Next, spread drained vegetables over chicken.
Mix soup with chicken broth and pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour on top.
Cook.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 6 adults (can double recipe easily).

title: surprise pie
directions: Add baking powder to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold in sugar.
Add nuts and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Store overnight in refrigerator. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in plastic bag in freezer until ready to use. To cook, place balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot as an appetizer.

title: creole stuffed squash
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery with tomato paste, water and margarine
until soft and slightly thick. Add salt to taste (add more water, if needed).
Cut off squash necks and cut out a wedge the length of the squash. Boil squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and place in small dish.
Fill depression in each squash generously with grated cheese.
Spoon sauce over all and cook in oven until cheese bubbles.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine and let stand for 30 minutes ground cucumber, onions, green peppers and salt.
Drain and add to vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and black pepper.
Boil 10 minutes and seal in jars.

title: gingered summer fruit compote
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and add pineapple juice gradually. Mix well until smooth.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Combine all fruit and toss with mixture gently until fruit is coated.
Refrigerate for up to 8 hours in covered container.
Spoon into serving dishes and garnish with fresh mint.

title: baileys
directions: Use 3 pints heavy cream and stir in all honey.
Add whiskey, chocolate syrup and remainder of cream.
Add vanilla slowly. Refrigerate.

title: teriyaki baked chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, garlic and ginger in a large bowl. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Marinate chicken for 4 hours or longer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Brush each piece with butter and place in shallow pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn over and add pineapple, onion and green pepper.
Return to oven.
Baste after 15 minutes.
Continue baking another 20 minutes.

title: no bake brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk and chocolate bits. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine strawberries, oil and eggs in a bowl.
In separate bowl mix sugar, flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and blend.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together shrimp, mayonnaise, milk, Worcestershire sauce, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole or large pan.
Top with crushed potato chips and almonds.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.
This can be refrigerated a day before baking.

title: pasta with broccoli and garlic(yields 8 servings)
directions: Cook pasta al dente. Drain.
Steam broccoli for 2 minutes. Rinse.
Put oil in skillet on medium heat for 1 minute.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 2 minutes. Add pasta and butter.
Cook for 3 to 4 additional minutes until all ingredients are mixed well and warmed.
Top with Parmesan cheese and salt to taste.
Can add shrimp (optional).

title: bread sticks a la bacon
directions: Take a slice of bacon and wrap the bread stick in a spiral fashion.
On a microwave safe plate, fit as many sticks as will fit with half-inch between sticks.
Count the prepared sticks and add 5 to that number.
This will give you your cooking time.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dice the potatoes and carrots into cubes about the size of 2 peas.
Cook them in boiling, salted water, together with the cut string beans and the peas, for about 6 to 7 minutes.
They should be barely tender, still firm.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour until smooth.
Add milk, oleo and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger meat with onion; drain.
Mix with tomato sauce and Good Seasons Italian dressing mix.
Add cooked spaghetti and stir well.
Put in dish.
Cover top with grated Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly warm.
Can mix ahead of time and refrigerate.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water and salt. Simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: pizza ryes
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Grate cheese and add to sausage; add spices.
Mix and spread on party rye bread.
Keeps real well in freezer.
Warm in oven when ready to use.

title: flavored coffees
directions: Mix well and use 2 teaspoonfuls (rounded) in 8 ounces boiling water.

title: fay's coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt into top of double boiler. Stir in cold milk. Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly. Cover and cook 15 minutes longer. Stir a little of hot mixture into the slightly beaten egg yolks, then add this to all the remaining mixture in double boiler. Cook for 2 minutes over hot (but not boiling) water, stirring constantly. Cool. Add vanilla. Stir in 1/2 cup chopped shredded coconut into cream filling before pouring into baked pie shell. Pour mixture in baked pie shell. Add meringue. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: holiday pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add green pepper, onion, pineapple, seasoned salt and 1 cup pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: coconut pineapple pops
directions: You will need 14 plastic cups or popsicle molds (3 ounces each), and 14 popsicle sticks.

title: penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Combine carrots, green peppers and onions in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown steak, after rolling in flour, in cooking oil.
Remove steak from pan and add tomatoes.
Stir to make a sauce and return steak to pan.
Cook in oven 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: dates exotic
directions: Open each date and stuff with a wedge of cheese.
Wrap with enough bacon to fasten with a toothpick.
Bake in oven at 300° until bacon is brown.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
This sauce is good on chicken and ribs.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Adjust oven rack 5 to 6 inches from bottom of oven. Cream butter while gradually adding sugar. Stir in vanilla first then flour and salt. Beat

until well blended. Stir in egg yolks and gradually add milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes. Reduce the heat to 325 degrees and bake another 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven to cool. Custard should be slightly soft in the center. It will become firm when it cools.

title: stuffin muffins(these savory bread puddings are absolutely scrumptious!)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 12-cup muffin pan.
Divide bread cubes among muffin cups.
In a large bowl, combine milk, eggs, scallions, thyme, salt and pepper.
Pour milk mixture over bread cubes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Run knife around puddings and carefully lift out.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots and raisins.
Toss gently.
In small bowl, combine mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Blend well.
Pour dressing over cabbage. Toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in sunflower seeds and bacon.
Serves 4.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add seed and raisins or currants.
Add milk and stir until dough forms a ball.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Shape into a 6-inch round loaf.
Put in greased layer cake pan or on a greased cookie sheet.
Cut an X in top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brush top with melted margarine after baking.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend together butter, cream cheese and sugar on low speed. Blend in eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into buttered and floured pans.
Bake 80 minutes at 325°.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and drain; add tomato sauce and taco seasoning. Sprinkle Fritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon hamburg mixture on Fritos.
Over this, add chopped onions, cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Mix soup mix and soup.
Spread mixture on beef.
Place in aluminum foil and seal (tented).
May use baking bag or roaster with lid instead.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: emporium beans
directions: Cook sausage in water for 1/2 hour.
Fry bacon until crispy. Fry onion and sausage until lightly browned.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours or cook in crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; knead with hands.
Pat or roll into circles, approximately 5 inches in diameter.
Fry in several inches of hot oil.
Dough will puff and bubble.
Turn when golden brown. Drain on paper towels and serve hot with honey or use for Navajo tacos.

title: pao de lo
directions: Beat the egg yolks with the sugar until smooth, then beat the whites separate.
When done, mix with yolks and sugar, then with a wooden spoon mix in the flour, salt and baking powder.
Bake in 9-inch nonstick pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Put all fruits into a dessert bowl.
Mix the vanilla pudding mix and Tang together with the reserved peach and pineapple juices until well blended.
Stir into the fruit.
Mix all together well. Chill and serve.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream shortening. Add next 4 ingredients and mix together. Add milk and vanilla.
Beat.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: clay recipe(overnight drying.  good for "cookie" ornaments.)
directions: Mix salt and water.
Stir and boil.
Add cornstarch and cold water.
Stir over heat until thick.
Use extra cornstarch on table and a rolling pin.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters. Use a straw for making a hole at the top for hanging.
Dry overnight and decorate with paint, glitter, etc.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Combine chicken soup, sour cream, onion and carrots.
Fold in cooked zucchini.
Combine and mix together the margarine and croutons. Spread half of crouton mix into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon on zucchini mixture.
Top with the rest of crouton mix. Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can also add leftover chicken.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until potatoes are done.
Add oleo and milk.
Season to taste.
You may cook 3 slices of bacon, chop up and put in soup, if you like.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add first 7 ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Add remaining ingredients together.
Cook to soft ball.
Pour on cake.

title: fillo sausage-egg bake
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine.
Saute red pepper, onion and mushrooms until tender.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Add to mushroom mixture.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in Monterey Jack cheese and mushroom-sausage mixture.
In another medium bowl, combine broccoli, Ricotta cheese and parsley flakes.

title: fruited tea
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add tea bags and mint leaves.
Cover and steep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Combine tea mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Let set overnight in refrigerator to enhance flavor.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a 12x7 inch casserole line bottom with hash browns.	Layer ham, onions, cheddar cheese on top of hash browns.	Beat eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over mixture.	Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Mix together the pork, onion, celery, rice, mushroom and chicken soups, water, mushrooms and soy sauce (adding a bit more water if you use fresh instead of canned mushrooms with their juice).
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covering the first 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 to 1 cup chow mein noodles over top for the last 20 minutes.

title: crab sandwich
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, remove and drain.
Saute mushrooms and onions in bacon drippings until the mushrooms begin to turn brown.
Cool.
Combine the crab, cheeses, and mayonnaise, then add to the bacon/mushrooms/onions mixture.
Spread the mixture on sliced, buttered muffins.
Place sandwiches on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.
You may substitute shrimp for the crab meat, if you wish.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Place softened cream cheese in large bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
If using cooked potatoes for mashing, add them while hot to the cream cheese.
If using instant potatoes, proceed to add your hot liquid and potatoes to the cream cheese as on instant potato package directions.
Beat until well mixed and smooth.

title: holly taters
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic bag; shake to coat potatoes. Place in baking pan, skin side down.
Drizzle melted margarine over potatoes and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Cream margarine, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Blend in flour.
Spread in bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine softened cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar. Blend in egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pan.
Combine the apples, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spoon over cream cheese. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: rainbow snowball cake
directions: Chill 10-inch tube pan.
With small scoop shape balls (strawberry cream and sherbets).
Place balls on cookie sheet; put in freezer until firm.
Soften vanilla ice cream.
Whip like fluffy whipped cream.
Arrange 1 layer of balls, adding vanilla ice cream to fill spaces.
Repeat to fill tube pan.
Freeze overnight.
Remove from pan.
Frost with whipped cream flavored with vanilla.

title: pizza stuffed peppers(4 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except peppers.
Cook and stir until Lite-line pieces melt.
Arrange peppers in shallow baking dish; spoon mixture into peppers.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chinese beef and broccoli
directions: Slice steak thinly in strips 1/4-inch wide and 2 inches long. Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and water or sherry together in small bowl.
Marinate beef in the mixture for 1 minute to 1 hour. Prepare broccoli; wash, remove outer skin and slice florets to about 1/4-inch thickness.
May slice upper stem into thin slices, also.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs; beat in flour.
Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes; spread. Sprinkle colored sugar over melted chocolate.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add nuts, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Frost as soon as icing is taken from heat; warm.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine margarine, flour and milk and cook until fairly thick. Remove from heat and add grated cheese.
Pour this mixture over drained asparagus.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread the top with cracker crumbs and brown.

title: banana oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Add the first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Add oatmeal and bananas.
When stirred well, add chocolate chips.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce deluxe salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin in boiling 7-Up.
Blend in applesauce.
When cool, pour into a serving bowl or mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with some cream or mayonnaise.

title: tofu salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350 degrees.
In sauce pan melt oleo, add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add water and stir again.
With wire whisk stir in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla, and milk.
Stir until smooth. Mix in pecans, and pour into 9 inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet for 50 minutes or until custard sets.

title: peanut butter chicken
directions: Make Italian dressing according to package directions. Marinate chicken in 1/4 cup dressing.
Cook pasta, rinse, drain and set aside.
Broil chicken just until done and set aside.

title: hot asparagus dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey burritos
directions: Brown turkey and drain.
Add taco seasoning and water; mix well.
Add beans; simmer until warm, adding water, if needed. Wrap mixture and desired toppings in tortillas.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Put 1/2 of mixture into bottom of a casserole dish.
Put chicken on top of mixture.
Mix soup, sour cream and broth together and season to taste.
Pour over chicken and top with remaining cracker crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly inside.

title: dirt dessert
directions: You will need a flowerpot and plastic or silk flowers.

title: zucchini relish(recipe originated in florida)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand overnight.
The next day, rinse, drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour into clean, hot jars and seal.
May not need all of the juice.

title: my chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large 4-quart pan in sausage drippings over medium heat.
Pulverize with large fork tines.
Add chili powder and onions.
Run 2 cans red or kidney beans beans through blender while adding pickle juice and 1 cup tomato juice.
Add to pot along with 2 cans whole kidney beans, garlic powder, celery salt, ground mustard, ground oregano, red pepper, sage and 2 cups tomato juice.
While stirring, add soy sauce and cumin.
While stirring to keep from sticking (over medium heat), bring to boil and remove from heat.
Add additional celery salt and plain or garlic salt, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beets with lemon and olive oil
directions: Bring a large quantity of water to the boil.
Add the beets and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes until done; drain.
Slip off skin. Slice or quarter the beets.
When ready to serve, heat olive oil (use butter if you wish) in a large pan.
Add the beets and heat thoroughly.
Blend in the lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: egg-a-roni salad
directions: Peel eggs and chop.
Mix remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Scoop centers out of tomatoes and fill with egg mixture.
Cool.
Serves 4.

title: old fashion lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cornstarch, whole eggs and egg yolks, lemon juice and rind in top of double boiler.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add remaining ingredients to egg whites with 2 tablespoons additional sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Cover top of pie and brown.

title: instant chocolate cookies
directions: Cook first five ingredients for one minute, then add peanut butter.
Stir in oats and immediately drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill, then serve.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered casserole.
Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pecan log
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Shape
into a log.
Roll in powdered sugar and wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In a large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups of flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, margarine and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour by hand.
Knead dough on floured surface about 1 minute.
Press or roll out to a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut dough into diamonds by cutting 2-inch diagonal cuts across dough.
Melt 1/3 additional cup of butter; dip each piece of dough into butter and place in bottom of tube pan.
Place enough pieces in pan to make first layer, then sprinkle with poppy seed.
Repeat until all dough pieces have been used.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Cool 2 minutes.
Invert.
Serve warm.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: These household hints were taken from my mother's 1938 Home Comfort (stove) Cookbook.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper. Add all ingredients and bake in oven (450°) for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together real well.
Put into casserole dish and put the topping on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruits of the sea
directions: Grease 2 quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Bake until bubbly at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
In casserole dish, place the raw rice; add the hamburger to the rest of the ingredients except the chow mein noodles.
Bake 1 hour covered at 350°.
Then pour over 1 can of chow mein noodles and bake 1/2 hour more uncovered.

title: peach sorbet with pineapple
directions: Place half of the peaches and 2 tablespoons apple juice at a time in food processor.
Cover and process until smooth.
Freeze at least 2 hours or until icy.
Scoop or spoon over pineapple slices.
If sorbet becomes too firm to scoop, remove from freezer about 1 hour before serving.
Makes 6 servings at 105 calories per serving.

title: chicken chip casserole(sisterhood banquet '94)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add 1 cup cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream; toss with chicken mixture.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered, or until hot.
Can be made ahead.
Refrigerate until baking time.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
Put as many as fill fit into microwave dish.
Cook on High for 5 minutes or until all meatballs in dish are cooked.
When all meatballs are done, drain.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Pat in seasoning and water for 15 minutes.
Take out and flour and brown in skillet, then add meat to water and seasoning.
Cook for one hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk all at once, stir to make a soft dough.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into stew (chicken, sauerkraut, etc.).
Cover; cook 12 to 15 minutes without removing the lid.

title: rhubarb dump cake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle white or yellow cake mix over.
Melt 1/3 cup butter; pour over cake mix.
Pour 1 cup warm water over cake.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.

title: orange julius drink(serves 4)
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 45 to 60 seconds.
Pour into chilled glasses and enjoy.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut cake slices into 3 pieces each; set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring to mix.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Arrange layers of cake slices, Jell-O mixture, pudding and Cool Whip in order given in a large punch bowl.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Chill for several days or overnight.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Boil rotini; do not overcook!
Drain and blanch with cold water; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Coat pasta with olive oil to prevent sticking.
Sprinkle pasta with Italian seasoning.
Cut green pepper; add to rotini.
Cut green onions; add to rotini. Cut and add artichoke hearts; also add the marinade to rotini. Cut and add pepperoni to rotini (be sure to skin first, if needed).
Drain and add black olives (whole).
Cut cherry tomatoes in halves and add to rotini.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered corn flakes or crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: sunset souffle
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and vegetables until they are done.
Debone chicken.
Thicken broth with cornstarch.
Line casserole with 1 crust.
Add all cooked ingredients.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° unti golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Layer, in dish, in order listed.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Saute onions but do not brown. Add eggs, crackers, milk, salt and pepper.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until it bubbles in middle.

title: chicken spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all 3 ingredients together well. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on crackers or party rye slices.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Put in greased tube pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Apply glaze to hot cake.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan well.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Crumble, brown and drain sausage.
Mix in cream cheese.
Trim crust off bread and spread a layer of sausage mixture on slice of bread.
Roll up jelly roll style, then cut each roll in half. Arrange on a cookie sheet, seam side down, and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until the bread is brown and toasty.

title: papa's anniversary punch
directions: Melt jello in hot water (dissolve good), add lemonade, sugar, pineapple juice and cold water.
Freeze till ready to use.
Thaw about 1 hour before ready to use.
Chop when slightly thawed, pour one (2 liter) bottle of ginger ale over mixture and stir well. Serves 30 people.

title: sausage-stuffed turkey breast
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove excess fat from turkey breast. Place turkey, skin side down, on plastic or waxed paper; unfold. Cover with plastic wrap and flatten to 3/4-inch thickness.
Mix remaining ingredients except margarine.
Place mixture lengthwise across center of turkey.
Bring long sides of turkey up around stuffing.
Tie with kitchen string.
Place turkey on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Brush with half or all of margarine.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Roast 1 hour; remove foil.
Brush turkey with remaining margarine.
Roast 45 minutes longer until golden brown and juices run clear.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: italian anise cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use ungreased pans.
Makes 6 dozen. Mix first 4 ingredients together then add flour and baking powder. Batter will be loose and sticky.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet.
I put 2 strips to 1 pan; they spread out.
When light brown on bottom, remove from oven with knife.
Make slices and put back in oven.
Brown on each side.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes well.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in saucepan to 300° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat. Add coloring and flavoring. Stand well back from pan so as not to inhale fumes. Pour quickly into 12 x 15-inch shallow pan that has been heavily filled with sifted powdered sugar. Begin cutting with scissors as quickly as you can lift a corner. Place pieces separately on wax paper that has been lightly sprinkled with powdered sugar. Seal in a tight container when completely cool.

title: coconut balls
directions: Corn syrup may be heated in microwave oven until hot, about 45 seconds. Add coconut to hot corn syrup; mix well.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight. Shape into balls with damp hands. Dip balls into chocolate. Colored chocolate may be used to make bonbons.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow	directions
of Solomon for bringing up a child; Proverbs 23:14.
Bake as a loaf cake in preheated oven at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until brown.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix and chill dough.

title: tutti-fruitti punch(non-alcoholic; makes 8 quarts)
directions: Saute chopped onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Sprinkle mixture on buttered toast (rye bread is especially good).
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with a combination of grated Swiss and Cheddar cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
A great luncheon sandwich.

title: date balls
directions: Cook in saucepan for 10 minutes slowly.
Make small balls and roll in coconut.

title: midwinter soup
directions: Dice potatoes.
Cook with cabbage about 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 15 minutes, slowly.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for a few minutes if hard to roll out.
Real good for apple pie; enough for bottom crust and lattice top.

title: salmon squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together (save 1 cup of corn flakes for top).
Bake in a 350° oven until set.

title: apricot salad
directions: Pour hot apricot nectar over jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add lemon-lime soda and stir.
To this, add the apricots, oranges, bananas and coconut.
Pour into a mold or individual molds and chill.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening/butter, sugar and blanched almonds.
Sift together and work in flour and salt. Chill dough. Roll with hands pencil thick. Cut in 2 1/2-inch lengths. Form into crescents on ungreased baking sheet. Bake until set, not brown.
Cool on pan. While slightly warm, carefully dip in 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixed. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 14 to 16 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add orange juice and rind.
Add egg.
Fold in diced cranberries and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350 degrees for 60 minutes or until golden.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Let broccoli thaw enough to separate with fork.
Mix soup, milk, butter and Cheez Whiz over low heat.
Add celery, onion and broccoli together.
Mix uncooked rice into all of this and put in large, glass pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Don't cover unless it browns too much.

title: lemonade syrup for homemade lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and add lemon juice.
Strain the syrup to remove unwanted pulp and seeds.
Store in covered glass jar in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, add 2 Tbsp. of syrup to 1 glass of cold water, stir to mix, add ice and enjoy.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of syrup.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Melt oleo.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix with vegetable mixture.
Stir in bacon bits and cheese.
Put into Bundt pan, ungreased.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: custard cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in a 9-inch skillet and heat in the oven.
Place dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add eggs, one cup of milk and buttermilk and mix.
Pour into hot skillet.
Very slowly, pour last cup of milk over the top of the batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom chicken bake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Pour crumbled Ritz crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Slice butter on top Ritz crackers.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 beaten egg and melted margarine by hand. Press the mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I use shortening, then flour; cake will not stick.)
Blend the cream cheese and 2 eggs well.
Add sugar until all these ingredients are mixed smooth.
Pour in cake layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: swedish chicken
directions: Partially fry bacon and cut into pieces.
Arrange dried ham pieces on bottom of casserole.
Place chicken pieces next and then bacon.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over meat layers.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and beat about 5 minutes on high speed; add butter.
Put into shell and bake at 325° until firm when shaken.

title: cowboy bean soup
directions: Wash and soak
beans
overnight.
Pour
off
liquid the next morning.
Add water and simmer about 1 hour.
Add all the rest, except the salt
and
refried
beans.
Simmer 2 hours or until tender.
Add refried
beans and salt to taste; simmer 15 minutes. Serve.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix together mashed figs, sugar and strawberry Jell-O.
Heat this mixture to a rolling boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars.

title: butter pecan bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray Bundt pan with cooking spray. Mix all ingredients together, using an electric mixer. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Check with toothpick for doneness. Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes. Loosen sides and invert on cake plate. Before serving, drizzle caramel topping on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: no-knead dinner rolls
directions: Pour the water into a mixing bowl.
Add the sugar and yeast; dissolve.
Beat in the egg and vegetable oil.
Add the flour and salt.
With a large spoon, beat this spongy dough until it is elastic and smooth.
Cover it with a damp towel or plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place for 1 hour.

title: chocolate whimsies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on wax papered cookie sheet and cool.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Layer in order given on platter or shallow dish.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Cook and pick chicken off bones.
Mix all ingredients together.
Keep out 1 cup cracker mixture to put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces.
Cook and drain.
Mix melted margarine, cut-up chicken or turkey, mushroom soup and sour cream together.
Put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle lots of Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: posie cream frosting
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix shortening and margarine. Then beat in sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy and light and spreading consistency.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn; pour into large, oversized bowl.
Combine butter, sugar, syrup and salt in heavy pan; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in condensed milk.
Cook over medium heat to thread or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; toss lightly and quickly with popped corn.
Form into balls or press into baking dish to cut into squares.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in dishpan in order given.
Drop by tablespoons and flatten.
Place 6 to 8 to a cookie
sheet.
Bake
in preheated 350° oven for 12 minutes, but do not overbake.

title: korean cabbage
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in oil.
If there is much excess water, pour off.
Mix sauce, sugar, toasted seed and red pepper. Pour over meat mixture and simmer one minute.
Quarter cabbage (or cut in smaller pieces); remove hard center.
Spread over meat and cook, covered tightly, until firm-tender.
Stir once.
If desired, throw in some cherry tomatoes a minute before serving.

title: baked ham glaze
directions: Mix together.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Put over or serve with ham.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chop bananas.
Pour pineapple and juice over and sprinkle Tang over these two.
Chop remaining ingredients and add juice (except mandarin orange juice, drain it off).
Sprinkle vanilla pudding over and stir.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package. Drain excess water. Melt cheese with vegetables. Add water chestnuts. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Melt butter with crumbled crackers. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain grease off.
Add sauce, soup and ketchup.
Add seasonings.
Boil for about 20 to 30 minutes. Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Drain and serve with sauce.

title: hot spiced cranberry tea
directions: Combine water, tea mix and cranberry juice.
Heat thoroughly. Serve hot in mugs with a lemon slice decorated with cloves.
Stir with a cinnamon stick.
Serves 6 cups.

title: any idiot can make fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and evaporated milk; stir and boil 8 minutes in boiler.
Stir Marshmallow Creme, chips and nuts.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Pour butter mixture over it.
Cut into squares.

title: hermits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Blend in egg, oil, molasses and water. Add raisins. Dough will be thick and hard to blend, but worth it. Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Brush with a beaten egg.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes. Hermits will be about 1 1/2-inches high, chewy and delicious.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and pat into dish on top of cooled crust (will not spread with a spoon).
Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Let chill overnight, if possible.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Combine eggs and sugar and beat. Add shortening and blend, then add flour and vanilla and blend. Shape into 3 rolls, 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap each in wax paper. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in thin slices with sharp knife and place on baking sheets, greased.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except corn bread mix.
After well mixed, add the corn bread mix and blend thoroughly.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done and browned enough.
Serves 20.

title: crunchy cocoa pie crust
directions: Crush cereal.
Combine with butter.
Press into sides and bottom of pie pan.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of mixture to sprinkle on top of pie for garnish.
Chill.
Fill with ice cream or chiffon filling.
Top with whip cream and garnish.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt margarine on medium heat and saute onions until clear and tender. Butter 2-quart 8 x 11 x 2-inch casserole dish. Reserve 3 tablespoons crumbs for topping. Line dish with remaining crackers. Add onions and soup, alternating until dish is full. Cover with beaten eggs and pour milk over top. Sprinkle with grated cheese and crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt butter and stir in powdered sugar.
Spread mixture on bread and cut into fourth layer in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Sprinkle onions in baking dish.
Press hamburger into dish. Sprinkle salt and pepper over hamburger.
Spread both cans of soup over hamburger.
Add Tater Tots on top and bake.
