Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend vanilla pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese; blend.
Put Oreo cookies through food processor until dirt like.
Layer in container with cookies first, then pudding, ending with cookies.
Add silk flower for decoration.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, using only 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Put in buttered baking dish and top with remaining stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sangria
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add fruit.
Pour into glasses and add ice.

title: peach crisp
directions: Toss peaches, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Spoon into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish and set aside. Combine flour and remaining sugar; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle on top of peaches. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: honey chicken & grape salad
directions: Mix dressing and orange peel in large bowl.
Add chicken breast strips, grapes and celery.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss with lettuce and sprinkle with sunflower seeds just before serving.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: First boil chicken; cool and pick off bones.
While chicken is cooking make noodles.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter, add garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Mix in grated cheese, season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until tortellini are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil and simmer 2 minutes.
Serve.
Additional cheese may be added.

title: christmas date squares
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water; cook all together until thick and put aside. Combine remaining ingredients thoroughly to make oat mixture. Put 1/2 of oat mixture into a pan and pat down. Layer the date mixture on top. Pour remainder of oat mixture on top. Bake in moderate oven until light brown.

title: sweet biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl and sift together.
In another bowl mix the other ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Mix well and roll small amounts into braids or round flat pieces and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
You can also substitute almond extract in place of lemon.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan; saute garlic and onion. Process tomatoes in food processor or blender.
Stir tomatoes and remaining ingredients into the saucepan.
Heat to boiling; simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Prepare Stock:
Wash beans and soak overnight (or boil for 1 hour); add to stock.
Mince onions and celery, carrots, green pepper, cabbage and garlic with French knife.
Place olive oil in stock pan and heat.
Add minced vegetables and garlic and saute until tender.
Add crushed tomatoes, stock, basil, oregano and simmer.
Add chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Season to taste.
Serve by sprinkling Parmesan cheese on top of each serving.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add milk and flour alternately a little at a time. Beat well and pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 375° until done.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate, marshmallows and milk; stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Chill 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Fold in whipping cream.
Turn into pastry shell.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and discard pit.
Mash avocados with fork in a bowl.
Add diced tomato and onion.
Squeeze most of the juice from the lemon half.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Get tortilla chips and share immediately; or, grab a spoon, sneak away and indulge right out of the bowl!

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil and deep fry 5 to 6 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Fry chicken in skillet without flouring. Cut up plenty of onions and garlic. Make a brown gravy. (If you want tomatoes, only add 1 spoonful of flour to gravy.) Add celery and parsley and cook until chicken is done and gravy is brown and thick. Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli and rice according to directions.
While these are
cooking, mix together mayonnaise, egg and cream of mushroom soup.
Add
cooked
broccoli
and
rice
to mixture. Soften
Cheez Whiz and mix with other ingredients.
Crush Ritz crackers good. Pour casserole in large dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Cook in 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: oven stew(venison or beef)
directions: Marinate deer
fillets in Dale's steak sauce for 1 or 2 hours. Wrap
a
piece
of bacon around each fillet.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook on grill until done.

title: mexican dip
directions: Chop lettuce fine.
Put layer of lettuce in bottom of dish. Mix beans and picante sauce together.
Spread over lettuce.
Add layer of sour cream.
Chop onions fine and sprinkle over sour cream.
Sprinkle grated cheese next.
Then top with chopped lettuce.
Decorate with tomato slices.
Stand chips around edge.

title: helen's apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; fold in apples.
Spread in greased 13
x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sunflower seed cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican pie
directions: Mix all and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Slice in thin pieces as a snack.
So good!

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Combine egg, milk, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and salt in order listed.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the nuts.
Set aside nuts to roll cheese ball in after other ingredients are mixed. Refrigerate. Serve on crackers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine and let boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and take off stove.
Add oatmeal; stir and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and set aside.
In small bowl, blend soy sauce into cornstarch; stir in sherry, ginger, sugar, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in 10-inch pan (nonstick coating).
Stir-fry green peppers and onions for 2 minutes; remove to bowl.
Stir-fry walnuts until golden and remove.
Add remaining oil and reheat, if necessary.
Stir-fry chicken 2 to 3 minutes.
Then stir in soy mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in vegies and walnuts.
Cook 1 minute, until heated through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water, corn syrup and raisins.
Cook and stir until bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and margarine.
Filling will be thin.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce temperature to 375° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: mut mix
directions: Put all of the fruit ingredients in a blender.
Add all of your liquid ingredients next and then your ice cubes.
Push puree on your blender and let blend for 2 to 3 minutes, making sure ice cubes are turned into slush.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat on low speed until well blended.
Cover; refrigerate dough 2 hours, or until firm enough to handle.
Heat oven to 375°.
Use about 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie; shape dough around each chocolate piece. Roll to make ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until cookies are set but not brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove to wire rack.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Roll again in powdered sugar just before serving. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; add the pretzels and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Mix the rest of the sugar with the other ingredients.
Stir the pretzel mixture into this and pour all of this into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: my clam chowder
directions: Lightly
brown bacon with onion. Drain off grease.
Add to the other
ingredients.
Heat.
Cool and put in refrigerator. Reheat.
Better if it stands before eating.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: request green beans
directions: Drain beans; save 1/2 can of juice.
Put layer of green beans, layer of onion rings and layer of cheese slices; repeat.
Pour can of mushroom soup over top and spread around.
Pour saved juice over top, put another layer of onion rings on.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strong vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients together and whisk.

title: quick green pepper steak
directions: Mix together 1 tablespoon each of the soy sauce, wine, oil and cornstarch in a small bowl.
Toss the beef strips in the mixture to coat.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a wok or frypan over high heat.
Add the meat and cook quickly to brown, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Set aside and add a bit more oil to pan and saute onion for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add bell pepper and cook for 1 minute more. Return meat to pan, along with tomatoes and broth.
Cook until broth boils.
Stir together the remaining soy sauce, wine and cornstarch.
Thicken broth with the cornstarch mixture.
Serve over boiled rice or pasta.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: take it easy chicken
directions: Mix rice with soups and water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 the onion soup on top.
Cover mixture with breasts.
Top with remaining onion soup.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hurry-up skillet meal
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package.
Brown hamburger, drain off fat, pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add green pepper, celery salt and pepper.
Add Rice-A-Roni, top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pinwheels
directions: Cook chicken with carrots, celery and onion.
Remove bones from chicken and mince the meat.
Mash with a fork the cooked carrots, celery and onion.
Save the chicken broth for gravy.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Put spices in Dutch oven.
Put in cut up chicken.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and beat.
In small bowl, combine coloring, cocoa and vinegar.
Add to egg mixture. Alternate flour and buttermilk, starting and ending with flour. Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick cheddar bread
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Add cheese. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: 3-bean salad
directions: Slice onion. Drain beans and toss lightly to mix.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans and toss lightly before serving. Very good!

title: pyracantha jelly
directions: Pick 2 pints of berries.
Wash well, then boil for 20 minutes in 3 pints water.
Let sit 1 minute, then skim off settlement.
Add juice of grapefruit and juice of lime or 1 tablespoon of concentrated lime juice.
Drain.
Do not squeeze!
This should make 4 1/2 cups of juice.
If not, add more grapefruit juice until it does.
Then add Sure-Jell and bring to boil.
Add sugar.
Boil hard for 2 minutes, or until jelly drops from spoon.
Pour into glasses and seal.

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Cook milk and sugar. Stir as starts to boil.
Continue to stir to keep from sticking. Add margarine after about 30 minutes.
Add vanilla and almond extract. Add butter flavoring. Add pecans after about 45 minutes.
Cook at least 1 hour and 25 minutes or until too hard to stir.
Pour into a buttered pan. Cut into pieces with knife.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop onions and pepper, then saute onions and pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
When done, add meat and brown.
Add the tomatoes, beans and seasoning.
Cook the rice and put all ingredients together in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased dish; cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: braz's best sugar cookies
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar
in a mixing bowl and set aside.
Combine sugars, butter and oil; cream well.
Add egg and vanilla to sugar and fold in all flour. Cover and chill overnight.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In large pan lightly brown beef and onions.
Add tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano. Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed.
Drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce, then alternate layers of lasagne, sauce and cheese, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; add eggs.
Mix and add both sugars and flour; add salt, soda and vanilla.
Form into balls.
Flatten with a fork dipped in milk.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spanish style omelet
directions: Preheat broiler.
Melt butter or margarine in a large, heavy skillet.
Add onion and bacon; saute until bacon is crisp and lightly browned.
Add potatoes and bell pepper; cook 2 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all ingredients, except nuts and chocolate chips, for 2 minutes. Pour into pan. Sprinkle nuts and chips over top and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon flavored squash
directions: Cook bacon, drain, crumble and reserve drippings.
Saute squash and onion in bacon drippings for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine egg and sour cream, and add to squash and onions.
Stir in half of bacon. Spoon half of squash mixture into shallow greased 2 qt. casserole. Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top.
Add other half of squash mixture. Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Sprinkle remaining bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mini fruit pizza
directions: Cream together cake mix, margarine and egg to make crust. Bake in greased muffin tins.
Use about a 1 1/2-inch ball of dough and press into bottom of muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Let cool before getting out of pan.
Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust and top with any flavor of prepared fruit pie filling.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces.
(This should take about 2 months.)
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene stove about 4 weeks at 450°.
This will feed 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add two rabbits.
But only do this in case of emergency, most people don't like hare in their stew.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and chill until partially set. Blend cream cheese and pineapple together and fold into gelatin with other ingredients, adding whipped cream last.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Take at least 20 minutes.
Shape into small balls and freeze in a plastic bag.
Use as many as you need.
Bake on greased pan at 325 for about 15 minutes, then turn and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: savory potato gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish, arrange in layers the potatoes and onions, sprinkling with garlic and seasoning in between layers.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream all over top.
Sprinkle with paprika, if used.
Increase temperature to 400° and bake another 10 to 20 minutes, until potatoes are fork-tender and slightly browned on top.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut Crisco in.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add along with the milk to dry ingredients.
Spoon onto greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, oleo and cream cheese.
Add one egg at a time with a little flour.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan. Don't preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham and cheese balls
directions: Chop onion very fine.
Tear one package ham into small pieces. Mix all ingredients except second pack of ham together.
Divide into two balls.
Cut last package of ham into squares.
Wrap cheese balls with ham squares.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: ever-ready biscuit mix
directions: Mix the dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Store in tightly covered container Shelf life is 3 months.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer.
Start and end with lettuce.
Top or seal with: Hellmann's Mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 cup cheddar cheese, Bacos.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil, lemon extract and orange juice.
Add flour and baking powder to liquids.
Mix well.
Have the pizzelle iron hot and drop by teaspoons onto iron for about 30 seconds or until golden brown.
Remove from iron carefully with a fork.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes in 325° oven.

title: peas and peanut salad
directions: Combine peas and peanuts in a mixing bowl.
In a small bowl, blend oil and vinegar.
Add to peanut-peas mixture.
Stir until well coated; then drain off excess oil-vinegar mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste; add the mayonnaise.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix water, jello and mayo.
Then add other ingredients.
Let jello set until firm.
May add nuts on top.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake according to package.
In saucepan, combine sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook until thickened.
Pierce cake.
Pour mixture on top.
Combine pudding and milk.
Beat cream, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread as icing over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle coconut over top before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 10-inch cast-iron skillet, boil water, Karo and sugar until mixture has a 5-inch thread or angel hair from spoon when lifted out of mixture.
Add peanuts and boil until peanuts turn a golden brown and make a cracking sound.
Remove from fire; add butter, salt and soda.
Stir quickly and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Combine soups and milk in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into saucepan and stir in cream and chives.
Heat just to boiling. Stir occasionally and stir in heated seafood and dash of Old Bay seasoning.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix
all ingredients, adding cornstarch mix last.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Drain oranges only. Beat eggs, butter and sugar until fluffy. Add bread, broken up into "small" pieces.
Add oranges and pineapple (with juice). Fold in. Cover top with cinnamon and/or nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken mulligan
directions: Pressure hen for 1 hour, then cool and debone.
Pressure onions and potatoes in broth for about 30 minutes.
Put hen back into broth in top.
Add corn and peas.
Simmer.
Add milk and butter.
This makes a large stew.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, sherry, soy sauce and ginger; bring to a boil.
Mix water and cornstarch; add to mixture.
Boil until thick.
Place in slow cooker.
Brown sausages and pour off liquid. Add sausages, pineapple and cherries to mixture; cook on low all night.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well on paper towel.
Combine remaining ingredients with sausage.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old timey fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and mix well. Stir until it comes to a boil.
Cook, stirring once in a while, until mixture forms a soft ball in cold cup of water.
Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 buttered plates.
Cool and cut.

title: shrimp butter - party spread
directions: Mix and blend well all ingredients.
Spoon into a decorative crock.
Cover and refrigerate jar for 24 hours.
Spread on thin sliced party rye or pumpernickel.
Will make 3 dozen open faced sandwiches.
Good, Good!

title: german raw apple cake
directions: Add the first 9 ingredients together and mix, then add apples last.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients on top of batter before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add 5 eggs, one at
a time, blending well after each addition.
Add flour, blending well after each cup.
Add milk, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir well.
Put into greased and floured tube cake pan. Place in cold oven and turn to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange sour balls
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add the juice, vanilla wafers and chopped nuts.
Roll into small balls and then roll balls in coconut.
Put into tin and store in refrigerator.

title: squash patties
directions: Place grated squash and onions in a colander and sprinkle with salt. Let stand in colander in sink until all moisture is gone. Add flour, cornmeal, black pepper, cheese, and egg - mix well.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make design with chunks of fruit.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix green onions, sour cream and cream cheese together.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer ingredients in order:
noodles, sour cream mixture and beef.
You should finish with beef on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Stir together squash, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt. Let set overnight.
Store in a colander; rinse with water.
Bring vinegar and spices to a boil.
Add squash mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Fill jars and seal.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla all together and put in baking dish.
Top with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: veal francaise
directions: In a frying pan, melt butter (enough to coat the pan). Prepare veal by dipping it in the egg batter and then dredge in flour on both sides.
Add lemon slices to melted butter in frying pan.
When the butter is nice and hot, add the veal.
Brown on both sides.
Then add the Marsala wine, chicken broth and lemon juice.
Cook for a few more minutes (until all juices are hot). Sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese on top.
Then top with lemons (already in pan).
Place on plate and top with remaining juice from pan.
Serve over spinach or with a side of pasta.

title: divinity nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, saltines (crushed fine), vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.
Spread with Cool Whip; add coconut.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon, not a mixer. Batter will be stiff.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
A moist cake; keeps several weeks.

title: campfire beans
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a crock-pot and slow cook.
Serve hot.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with Cool Whip and nuts. Chill one hour.
A 9 x 13-inch pan may be used.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease
casserole dish, mix first 5 ingredients and place chicken on top.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup, seal with foil and bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Don't peek!

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in all but ham.
Divide into 5 parts.
Spread mixture on each ham slice.
Roll ham lengthwise.
Place seam side down on plate.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Remove from freezer.
Slice into 8 pieces.
Insert toothpicks through each slice.
Makes 40 pinwheels.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in bacon drippings in a nonstick pan.
Add rice and mix with onions and mushrooms and stir well. Add soy sauce, bacon and seasonings.
Stir well until fully mixed and hot.

title: easy chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and margarine over low heat until margarine is melted.
Add beaten eggs, milk and cornmeal.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: callaway gardens' cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to regular directions.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Add onion and cook until meat is about half done.
Cut cabbage in chunks and add with the carrots, tomatoes and potatoes.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Cook, tightly covered; add enough water to cover meat.
Cook over low heat about 2 hours.

title: dreamsicle pie
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Pat half into bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Spread half of orange sherbet into plate, then all of vanilla; top with remaining sherbet.
Top off with remaining crumbs.
Freeze several hours before serving.

title: colorful beverage
directions: Pour the orange juice into ice cube trays and freeze them. Chill the cranberry juice in the refrigerator.
When the orange juice cubes are frozen, Place them in a large pitcher and pour in the cranberry juice.

title: old-fashioned southern tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and dry ingredients.
Blend well.

title: chicken-broccoli skillet
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Season chicken with garlic powder, pepper and no-salt season mixture for meats.
Cook chicken and green onion quickly in hot margarine until just done.
Stir in broccoli, lemon juice and thyme.
Cook, covered, for 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Cook, covered, for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine cooked spinach, soup, Cheddar cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Add spices.
Pour into an 8-inch square glass pan.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with mixer until smooth.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Bring to boil 1 cup Kahlua, sugar and margarine until sugar dissolves.
Stick cake with fork or toothpick several times, then pour hot mixture all over cake, while cake is still warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer onion in butter.
Add all other ingredients and simmer about 5 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugar, baking soda and half and half in large saucepan on stove.
Bring to soft boil stage (240° on candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Turn off stove; let set.
When settled, beat with electric mixer until smooth (it will be thin).
Add vanilla and pecans as it thickens.
Spoon out on wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about 18 pralines.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Whip all together and place in baking dish.
Cover with topping.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Soften the unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup water in large saucepan.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups water, the lemon pudding mix and the sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Chill until mixture mounds from spoon.
Pour 2/3 cup undiluted Carnation evaporated milk into ice tray or 8-inch cake pan.
Chill in freezer until soft crystals form around edge (10 to 15 minutes).
Whip until stiff (about 1 minute).
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Whip very stiff (about 2 minutes longer).
Fold into cooled pudding.
If pudding is lumpy, beat until smooth.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours, or until firm.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill chicken breast until tender.
Cut into small blocks or shred.
Cut up all ingredients for bite size bites.
Combine in bowl and enjoy.

title: chocolate cream pudding
directions: Mix the cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add cold milk.
Stir thoroughly.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook in double boiler 8-10 minutes stirring constantly until custard thickens.
Melt chocolate in hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Add to mixture.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Saute onions and celery in butter. Add the Cheez Whiz and melt.
Add the mushroom soup and cook on low until heated good.
Then mix all ingredients well.
May top with grated cheese and bake if you want too.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine egg and milk, put aside. Combine dry ingredients. Dip tomato slices in egg then in dry ingredients. Heat oil in large skillet. Place prepared tomato slices in oil and fry on medium heat until brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings or butter.
Add eggplant and tomatoes mashed with fork or masher.
Add eggs.
Stir until it looks like scrambled eggs.
Stir in cheese.
Add 3/4 cups crumbs and pour into baking dish and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: surprise pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Let cool.
Sprinkle nuts in baked pie shells.
Add sliced bananas.
Pour pineapple mixture over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut on top of Cool Whip.
Cool 2 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions for 9x13-inch cake pan.
Pierce cooled cake with wooden spoon handle.
Drizzle condensed milk and sauce over cake.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with candy.
Chill until serving time.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and food color to sugar and egg mixture. Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: curried vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours for flavors to blend.

title: congealed beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid. Place beets in food processor; process until pureed. Combine reserved beet liquid, vinegar and onion in saucepan and bring to a boil. Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling liquid. Remove from heat. Stir in beet puree and horseradish. Pour mixture into lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce. Garnish with a dollop of mayonnaise and a sprig of parsley. Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Heat 2 1/2 cups milk. Pour 1/2 cup milk into dry ingredients to make a paste.
Add paste to warm milk; cook and stir constantly.
Cook until thick.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add 2 tablespoons hot mixture to eggs.
Then add eggs to warm mixture.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Cut 2 bananas into mixture and pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Garnish top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in butter.
Stir in flour, salt, paprika and tomato puree or sauce.
Add chicken broth.
Cook until bubbly.
Add other ingredients and serve over rice.

title: atkins onion soup
directions: Melt butter and add oil.
Add onions.
Cook slowly until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and flour. Stir for 2 minutes and add bouillon water.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Place toasted bread in bowl; add half bowl of soup. Place cheese on top of bread and fill rest of way with soup. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate-date-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Next, add flour and soda.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes. Cool 1 minute, remove to wire rack.

title: ruth pullen's frozen liver pate
directions: Mix braunschweiger, 1 package of cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 tablespoon mustard until smooth.
Shape into log roll and chill.
Combine and mix 2 packages of cream cheese and 1/2 tablespoon of mustard.
Spread over sausage.
Chill.

title: yeast biscuits (gail's)
directions: Blend together sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together, including flour.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Make rolls and let rise for a few minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soft and simple pretzels
directions: Defrost frozen rolls in the refrigerator overnight or at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Shape each roll into a 12-inch strip. Twist each strip into a pretzel shape.
Let rise, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and pork
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in pot; add spareribs.
Simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Best when reheated.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix meat, rice, onions, crumbs and egg together.
Form meat balls, place in baking dish.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. (Time will depend on size of meat balls.)

title: banana smoothies
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Whirl until smooth.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut bottom half of hot dog bun in 2 sticks. Cut top in 3 sticks. Heat margarine. Add spices to melted margarine. Put bread on cookie sheet. Brush oil over with mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 250°.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Process at medium speed until smooth in blender.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.
Frozen fruit makes thicker shakes.

title: tucson breakfast burro(healthy recipe)
directions: *(Substitute a 15 ounce can black or pinto beans, drained, for Manchaca for a non-meat protein.)

title: meat balls(kjottkaker)
directions: Soak crumbs in milk; add onion, egg yolks and seasonings; mix well.
Add meats and blend well.
Shape into large balls and brown well in butter.
Add boiling water and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mississippi mist pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter in small bowl.
Press firmly on bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate until firm. Reserving 3 strawberries for garnish, cut off stem ends of remaining berries so they are no more than 1-inch tall.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk; beat well.
Add lime juice and liqueur; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust, covering strawberries.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: crunchy chocolate candy clusters
directions: Melt chips and marshmallows over hot water in double boiler. When this is done, add other ingredients.
Mix.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: "kart-wheels"
directions: Heat the oven to 375°. Mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms. (If dough seems dry, mix in more milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.)

title: oven fried potato sticks("kiddie sticks")
directions: Cut each potato into 8 to 12 wedges.
Toss with oil and paprika.
Spread in shallow pan.
Bake until tender (about 20 to 30 minutes) at 450°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line a pie plate with pastry.
Cream together the butter and sugar; add beaten eggs, flour, salt, vanilla extract and Karo syrup.
Stir well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pastry and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, vanilla, and eggs until fluffy.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain
orange
sections,
reserving syrup. Add water to syrup to
make
cup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add measured liquid and chill until slightly thickened.
Blend sour cream
and
mayonnaise
into gelatin;
chill again until thickened.
Fold
in
orange
sections, marshmallows and nuts. Spoon into 8-inch square pan or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and freeze until firm.
Unmold and
garnish
wtih
crisp salad greens and additional fruit, if desired.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: quick company pie
directions: Mix all together and fill two 9-inch graham cracker crusts; refrigerate.

title: super shrimp
directions: In boiling water, cook shrimp 2 to 3 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Cool, peel and devein, leaving tails on as handles.
Place in double freezer bags.
Pour the bottle of Italian dressing over the shrimp in bag.
Close bags and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Dredge chicken in flour. Brown chicken in oil on all sides. Drain on paper towels.
Put chicken in casserole dish.

Add sauce and mushrooms. Use enough sauce to cover chicken. Heat in microwave on High for 5 minutes. Then reduce temperature to 50% power and heat for 10 to 15 minutes or heat completely in crock-pot or oven.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine egg, 1 3/4 cups eggnog and oil. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until combined.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cover with foil after 50 minutes if bread browns too quickly.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.
Wrap bread; store overnight.
To serve, stir together powdered sugar and enough eggnog to make of drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over bread.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an ungreased 9 X 13 cake pan. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool. Top with cool whip.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Have shortening at room temperature.
Assemble all ingredients and utensils needed.
Grease 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Pit and drain prunes.
Sift flour once before measuring.
Preheat oven to baking temperature.
Sift together the first 7 ingredients.
Put the next 3 ingredients into large bowl of Mixmaster.
Beat on Number 8 speed for 1 1/2 minutes, scraping bowl while beating. Stop mixer.
Add prunes, then add sifted flour mixture alternately with buttermilk or sour milk, while beating on Number 3 speed. Scrape sides of bowl while beating and beat only enough to blend, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pans.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill tart pastry shells about 1/2 full.
Makes approximately 18 larger tarts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add hash browns.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Spread on top of potatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: basic crepes
directions: Beat ingredients in mixing bowl until smooth.
Let batter set for 1 hour.
Next, oil a 7-inch (or 5) crepe pan and heat it until a drop of water sizzles when dropped (use about 3 Tbsp of batter). Add all at once, turning and tilting pan to cover area.
Turn crepe when browned.
Remove when done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: antipasto dressing
directions: Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a small bowl; stir well with a whisk.

title: championship cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and brown sugar. Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in chopped candy bars and oats. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased or parchment-lined baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: about 5 dozen.

title: meaty rye snacks
directions: Cook beef and sausage until crumbly.
Drain.
Cut cheese into small cubes.
Add to meat until melted, stirring constantly. Stir in seasonings.
Spread on party rye.
Freeze.
When ready to use, bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lucille ball's christmas persimmon cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in vanilla.
Add persimmon pulp and orange rind; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix in walnuts, raisins and dates.
Turn batter into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours (until cake tester comes out clean).
Turn out onto wire rack. Garnish, if desired, with fruit and nuts down middle of loaf. Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: spareribs in sauce
directions: Brown ribs on both sides and drain grease.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and put ribs and sauce into a roasting pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serve with potatoes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, broccoli, cream-style corn, onion, salt and pepper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together in a slow cooker and cook on low for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Mix well.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gingered chicken and almond stir-fry
directions: Combine 2 tablespoon soy sauce and 2 tablespoons cornstarch with chicken in a bowl.
Stir and refrigerate.
Combine broth, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and ginger in a bowl; set aside.
Stir-fry vegetables in 2 tablespoons oil until tender-crisp.
Remove to strainer.
Add 2 tablespoons oil and crushed red pepper to skillet and stir-fry chicken until no longer pink.
Stir in broth mixture; cook until it thickens and begins to boil.
Stir in vegetables and almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in pan large enough to hold them in a single layer.
You do not brown the meat first.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in chunks.
Layer on top of the meat. Now mix tomato sauce, water and sugar.
Pour over.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Last of all scatter tapioca on top.
Don't bother to stir in.
Seal tightly in heavy foil.
Place in a 325° oven for at least 2 hours.

title: bertha's banana pudding
directions: Beat vanilla pudding and milk until firm.
Add Cool Whip.
Add sour cream.
Line bottom of pan with wafers and top with bananas. Pour pudding over wafers and bananas.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Brown the ground beef; season with salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Pour rice in meat; roll into balls.
Place balls in casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over meatballs.
Add a little water in the bottom of the dish.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: lemonsnaps
directions: In a bowl using an electric mixer, cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg, lemon zest and almonds.
Beat in flour, a little at a time until thoroughly blended.
Cover bowl and chill for about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350° when ready to bake. Lightly grease baking sheet.
Shape dough into balls, walnut-size and place on prepared sheet about 2 inches apart.
Flatten each cookie by moistening the bottom of a glass, dipping it in sugar and pressing it down on each cookie.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden at edges.
Cool on racks.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: erin's no-bake cookies
directions: Cook the sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and pinch of salt for 1 minute.
Stir in oatmeal, vanilla, peanut butter and coconut. Drop onto cookie sheet that has been covered with wax paper.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Heat iron skillet.
Add 1/4 cup of oil.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in heated skillet; cover with grated cheese.
Pour rest of mixture on top and bake at 475° for 40 minutes or
until well browned.
This is a big recipe so it's better to use two 8 or 10-inch skillets.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls, about the size of a small nut, then brown.

title: 7-up chili burgers
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion flakes.
Drain off excess fat. Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Slowly add 7-Up.
Stir until smooth and add to meat.
Then add the chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie for my sister
directions: Mix gelatin and spices and salt into a medium saucepan.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour into pan with dry ingredients. Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until dissolved, about 10 minutes or so.
Remove from heat; stir in pumpkin and Equal.
Pour mixture into a baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: panic
directions: Pour pie filling into greased pan or flat shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Pour melted butter evenly over cake mix.
Top with nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, half and half or ice cream.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill so flavors mix.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: fix ahead casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
In large bowl, mix cottage cheese, Cheddar, onions, chives and mushrooms.
Mix meat with spaghetti sauce in another bowl.
With casserole dish, place sauce/meat mixture to cover bottom.
Add layer of uncooked noodles, layer of cottage cheese mix, layer of noodles, layer of sauce mix. Continue until casserole is full.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan. Freeze or put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
If frozen, thaw before baking or add 30 minutes to cooking time.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream margarine and shortening. Beat in sugar and milk alternately. Beat vigorously until granules cannot be felt between fingers (on high speed with electric beater for 10 minutes). Blend in vanilla.

title: red beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; brown the beef in the butter. Add sliced mushrooms and onions.
Cook until onions are tender. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add broth and tomato paste. Stir.

title: hot corn dish
directions: Mix together corn, Bisquick mix, egg, butter and milk.
Pour half of batter into greased pan (8 x 8-inch).
Cover with shredded cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt shirley's caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn into a large, shallow pan.
Place in a slow oven (250°) to keep warm and crisp.
In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Boil to firm ball stage (248°) about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Syrup will foam.
Pour hot caramel mixture over popped corn in a fine stream.
Mix well.
Return to oven for 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and serve or store in airtight container.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Pour 1 can of fruit (any kind) in dish.
Mix 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Alternate layers of oysters, crackers and dots of margarine, ending with a layer of crumbs. Add milk until liquid almost reaches top of casserole.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: no sugar cookie
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes on low heat.
Add margarine, cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
A pecan or walnut may be placed on each cookie.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Heat margarine, water, and cocoa over low heat.
Do NOT boil. Mix flour, sugar, and salt and pour chocolate mixture into this. Then mix all other ingredients together.
Batter will be very thin.
Bake in a 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Let cool.

title: favorite holiday cake
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add coconut and marshmallows.
Boil over heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Spread over cake layers.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot; bring to boil.
Simmer 3 hours or until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: southwestern cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Mix dry ingredients together and make a well in the center.
Add eggs, butter and sour cream and blend thoroughly.
Fold in corn kernels. Pour half of the batter into pan.
Cover with grated cheese and chiles.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: walnut spice cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except walnuts and frosting, on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: cowboy dip
directions: Melt cheese with milk.
Keep warm in a heated crock-pot. While melting, brown beef.
When brown, add to cheese in pot.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, bell pepper and picante sauce and stir.
Serve with your favorite chips or use with noodles for a Mexican casserole with flair.

title: easy sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water for 5 minutes.
Sift together 3 times the flour, salt, soda, sugar and baking powder. Cut in shortening until fine.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to flour mixture until moistened good.
Roll out on floured cloth about 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with soft butter; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mix over the butter.
Leave plain or sprinkle with nuts or raisins.
Roll up; cut about 1-inch thick.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, about 12 to the pan.
Let rise 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 12 to 15.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: stuffed chicken breasts italiano
directions: Carefully slit a lengthwise pocket in each chicken breast, starting at the thick side, cutting approximately 3/4 of the way through the width of each breast.
Season the inside and outside of each breast with salt and pepper.
Combine Ricotta cheese with olives, parsley, onion and garlic salt.
Place approximately 1/4 cup of this filling into each breast.
Arrange stuffed breasts in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and cover with pasta sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over the top and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve on fettucini.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fill 6 mini loaf pans or 2 regular loaf pans half full.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large pot, brown beef, onions and celery.
When browned, add 1 quart canned tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 2 hours, then add all vegetables.
Cook an additional hour.

title: kraft macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to the directions on the box.
Add 2 eggs and pour in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Pour pizza sauce, cheese and pepperoni on top.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Cut in squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Return to a 350° oven and bake another 10 minutes.

title: coconut butterball
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour.
Add vanilla; beat.
Stir in coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until delicately browned.
While cookies are still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes approximately 4
dozen cookies.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Stir chopped vegetables into pasta.
Add Italian dressing and mix well.
Add McCormick Salad Supreme and mix well.
Chill at least 3 to 4 hours to let flavors combine.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Bake cake.
While cake is baking, mix pineapple and sugar together.
Poke holes in hot cake (generously) and pour pineapple mixture over cake.
Refrigerate until cool.
Make pudding and add coconut to pudding.
Pour over cooled cake.
Mix almonds with Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Keep cake refrigerated!

title: clam and corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart saucepan.
Add onion; cook until soft. Stir in chopped or minced clams, clam juice, creamed corn, milk and Tabasco.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until hot.
Do not boil.
Garnish with fresh parsley or bacon bits.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and salt; drain. Saute onion and bell pepper.

Add tomatoes. Be sure tomatoes are chopped. Add tomato sauce and water. Add Worcestershire sauce, A.1. Steak sauce, 1/8 cup sugar and garlic salt or powder. Add sauteed onions and bell pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Drain beans; dump all ingredients into crock-pot.
Stir. Cook on low for 4 plus hours.
Check after 2 hours and add additional ingredients to taste.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions.
Cut out a deep hole in the center of each.
Chop removed part and mix with remaining ingredients.
Meanwhile, boil onions in salted water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain onions and fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Mix pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Boil to full rolling boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo immediately and stir.
Let stand 5 minutes and pour into jars.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: artichoke-shrimp soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti factory spaghetti mizithra
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender, but firm to bite.
Drain.
Melt butter in large skillet until butter turns brown in color. Meanwhile, combine cheeses.
Place spaghetti on platter.
Sprinkle with mixed cheeses, then drizzle with browned butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spice drop cookies
directions: Blend together cake mix, applesauce, salad oil and egg.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Mix in raisins and nuts, then place dough in refrigerator for several hours.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add taco sauce and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly and continue to beat until thick and glazed.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts slowly.
Drop batter by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Put cookies in oven and close door. Turn off the heat and leave overnight.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze to drain. Combine with other ingredients.
Mix well. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll into small balls, then roll balls in coconut. Store in covered container in cool place.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Thaw and drain peas. Layer bottom of dish with lettuce, then layer chopped onions, peas and bacon. Spread mayonnaise. Top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Wash squash and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Nature's Seasons and dot with margarine.
Add about 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook in microwave oven 15 minutes at medium temperature.

title: apple butter
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cook on low 15 hours.
Pour in 1 pint jars.
Will freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: suzanne's manicotti with beef
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic powder (drain).
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayonnaise; mix well.
Cook manicotti shells as directed on package, drain and cool on wax paper.
Stuff each shell with beef mixture and place in lasagna-size baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick sweet-sour pork
directions: Coat pork cubes with flour, salt and pepper; mix.
Stir-fry with peanut oil for 4 to 5 minutes until brown.
Add carrots; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover for 1 minute.
Add green pepper; stir-fry 1 minute.
Cover for 1 minute.
Add pineapple chunks and sweet-sour sauce.
Cover and simmer on low until sauce is heated. Serve over white rice.

title: hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lazy man's pudding
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Pour into baking dish. Spread fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and form ring. Place the jalapeno jelly in middle. Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in large bowl until frothy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar and beat.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in saucepan 10 or 15 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix over pear mixture.
Slice 2 sticks margarine on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat egg until fluffy; add spices. Mix well.
Add soda and cocoa.
Alternately add flour, milk and mashed potatoes.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Make 2 or 3 layers.
Frost with chocolate frosting, topped with nuts.

title: pineapple-cranberry mold
directions: Drain crushed pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with pineapple juice (1 3/4 cups) in pan.
Bring to a boil. Stir in jello until dissolved.
Break up cranberry sauce and add to jello.
Stir in 3/4 cup pineapple juice.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened.
Add crushed pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10 x 4-inch tube pan. Beat sugar and butter in large bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and baking soda. Beat into sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk until well blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice; spread in pan.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool 20 minutes.
Invert on wire rack.
Remove pan.
Cool cake completely.
Spread glaze over top of cake, allowing some to drizzle down side.
Serve with fresh fruit and sweetened whipped cream if desired.

title: breakfast in a loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 2-inch slice from top of loaf.
Set aside for lid.
Remove soft interior of loaf, leaving a 1-inch thick wall and bottom.
Place meat in bottom of loaf.
Top with bell pepper rings.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheeses.
Layer scrambled eggs and tomatoes over cheeses.
Top with remaining cheeses and mushrooms.
Place top lid on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add sugar, pecans and coconut; also, half the juice of the pineapple. Place pineapple slices in square baking dish or baking pan. Pour mixture of margarine, pecans and coconut over slices of pineapple. Mix lemon flavor cake mix, water, eggs and rest of pineapple juice. Beat for 3 to 4 minutes. Pour batter over pineapple slices and other mixture in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in boiler. Add flour, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth. Boil macaroni at the same time you are preparing this sauce. Add milk to flour mixture; stir slowly and constantly over low to medium heat, being careful not to scorch. Stir until smooth and thick. Add cheese which has been grated. Drain macaroni noodles.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan; place noodles in the pan. Pour cheese sauce on top. Add extra shredded cheese and bread crumbs. Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and mash.	Beat cheese until smooth. Add potatoes and other ingredients except paprika. Slowly add sour cream (quit early if soupy). Spoon into lightly buttered casserole dish.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Preheat over to 425 degrees.
In large bowl mix water and yeast until dissolved.
Add beaten egg and stir well.
Stir in shortening and sugar; mix well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into greased muffin tin do not wait for these to rise.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown. Extra batter can be stored in a covered bowl in the refrigerator for up to one week.
Yield:
36 to 48 rolls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water; let stand until it practically sets. Add rest of ingredients. Pour into mold.

title: quick and easy green beans
directions: If using fresh beans, wash and clip ends.
Cover with enough water to boil string beans.
Cut onions and put appropriate seasonings.
Put all other ingredients in except potatoes.
Put potatoes in the last 35 minutes and cook until it's to your liking.

title: zucchini tempters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
In bowl, mix ingredients with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 cup salad oil; mix.
Spoon into prepared dish and bake 35 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: grandie's coconut pies
directions: Makes 2 (9-inch) pies. Cook at 350° until done.

title: muddie's banana nut bread
directions: *Substitute milk with a few drops of lemon and let stand 5 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Boil the ingredients and add your beets.
Bring to a boil and seal.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: May use fresh apples, peaches, blackberries, blueberries or canned peaches, partially drained.

title: low-fat black beans and rice
directions: Heat beans and rice in a microwave.
Mix together and serve. Only 1.5 grams of fat.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: no bake blueberry pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch pie shell and cool.
Wash the blueberries and put aside 2 1/2 cups.
Coat the remaining 1 1/2 cups of blueberries with the sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook slowly until thickened. Remove from stove, add the butter, lemon juice and cinnamon, mixing carefully.
Pour the 2 1/2 cups of blueberries into baked pie shell; then spread cooked berries over them.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot tamale bake
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain; add other ingredients and simmer until well blended.
Add water if too dry.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with a thin layer of corn bread batter (2 cups self-rising meal, 1 egg and 1 cup milk).
Bake in a 425° oven until browned on top.

title: bill's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Punch holes in top. Put ketchup on top with liquid from tomatoes.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and pour off liquid.
Bake uncovered for about 30 minutes until done.
Let cool for a few minutes and serve.

title: beef barbecue
directions: If using ground beef, brown and drain off grease before adding other ingredients.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Turn meat to coat all sides.
Place over medium heat and bring to a bubble.
Reduce heat.
Cover tightly.
Simmer until fork-tender. Turn meat several times during cooking.
Add water as needed to keep sauce at desired consistency.
Requires at least 3 hours cooking time.
Remove brisket to cutting board and shred in small pieces.

title: pizza sub sandwich
directions: Any other item you might like to top a pizza with.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and celery.
Put into large pot.
Wash and drain chop suey mix.
Add to other pot.
Add 1 cup water. Cook over low heat about 40 minutes or until celery is cooked. Drain.
Cut pork steaks into 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Flour, then brown in a large skillet.
When meat is almost done, add a can of mushrooms and finish cooking.
Add meat to other ingredients; mix well.
Pour over crispy or soft noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan (spray with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use dip Fritos.

title: vienna roast
directions: Marinate chicken or beef with salt and set aside.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese thoroughly.
Spoon on crust; slice bananas on top, then add the pineapple.
Cover mixture with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped pecans and cherries.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash berries; slice in half lengthwise or quarter large berries.
Measure 4 cups.
In kettle, combine berries and 4 cups sugar; let stand 15 minutes.
Add remaining sugar.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Boil hard, uncovered, 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin.
Skim off foam. Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Cover with wax.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in oil in large skillet or wok.
Add water and salt; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple and vegetables; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in apricot preserves, vinegar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: avocado vegetable mix salad
directions: Combine corn, avocados, eggs and onion.
Blend together remaining ingredients.
Toss mayonnaise mixture lightly with avocado mixture.
Garnish with sliced, pitted ripe olives, if desired.

title: school punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: taco or frito salad
directions: Cut up all salad ingredients.
Drain Ranch Style beans and rinse, then add to the salad ingredients with Fritos, Catalina dressing and grated cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: "forgotten chicken"
directions: Combine rice, soups and milk in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a medium-size saucepan, remove from heat.
Melt butter.
Mix cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Press half of batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top; drizzle with caramel. Crumble with remaining batter on top of caramel.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
The batter won't look done, but it is. Cool completely before cutting.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Saute onion and parsley in butter until onion is golden.
Add lobster meat.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and tomato paste.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove the parsley.
Add the cream.
Season to taste with salt and cayenne. Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: banana bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese at room temperature.
When soft, mix butter and cheese with all other ingredients.
Spread onto muffin halves.

Place muffin with spread on a cookie sheet and place into freezer for 1 hour. Remove and quarter the muffins with a sharp knife. Place muffins on cookie sheet into the broiler for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Do not overcook.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda; blend.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs and mix well.
Add green chiles and cheese and stir.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, Crisco, eggs and molasses.
Blend well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices; gradually blend into molasses mixture.
Blend
in hot water.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Best if served warm with Cool Whip.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange chicken
directions: Season chicken well with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste. Mix together orange preserves, Russian dressing and package of dry onion soup.
Cook mixture for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over the chicken and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. (Uncover chicken for last 20 minutes.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven fried teriyaki chicken
directions: Cover shallow baking pan with foil.
Soak chicken in the teriyaki sauce about 2 hours. Drain well. Drop chicken in mayonnaise and coat both sides of chicken with crumbs.
Place in pan. Bake 15 minutes, turn and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes or until done and browned.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: For sour milk, use the maraschino juice, add a Tbsp. vinegar, add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Cream oleo and sugar. Add egg and beat. Add sour milk alternately with flour, soda and salt.	Stir in melted chocolate and maraschino cherries.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Pour all but nuts into unbaked pie shell.
Add walnuts.
bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cool fruit pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice until thick.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit.
Nuts are optional.
Pour into crusts.
Let stand until firm.

title: fruit smoothy
directions: Put fruit in a blender. Add yogurt and blend. If too thick, add a little water (not much) until it reaches the desired thickness. Place in glass and put whip cream on top. This is simple and full of nutrition. Kids love this as a dessert.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until almost done.
Put a little bit of sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, put a layer of noodles (3 across).
Put some sauce on top of noodles.
Put half of the cottage cheese on next, then Colby cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Layer everything in order as first layer.
On last layer, put everything but cottage cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo.
Add all the other ingredients to make a batter. Pour batter over the oleo.
Then pour fruit over the batter.
Bake until done.
Crust will be on top when done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Hollow out mushrooms, tops and stems; crush tops and stems. Mix with other ingredients.
Stuff tops with mixture and bake on cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with diced onion, carrot and celery.
Let cool. Remove chicken from bones.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix 1 cup chicken broth, chicken soup and celery soup; pour over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Melt 1 stick of margarine. Crush the Ritz crackers; mix with margarine.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° until it begins to bubble.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Season chicken with spices.
Combine sour cream and mustard. Coat chicken well and roll in pecans and bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Garnish.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together, shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: wedding salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until marshmallows are melted. Cool.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple.
Cool until partially set.
Add cabbage, nuts and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipping topping. Set.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick, but not real stiff.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Put mixture in baked pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Saute sausages, onions and pepper.
Add other ingredients. Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 bean can of water.
Cook about 30 minutes.
(Use Garcia's bean soup if can't find the beans.)

title: poached sausage with hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until fork-tender.
Score sausage 1/4-inch deep every 2 inches.
In large skillet, bring to boil the water, bouillon cubes, 1/2 cup onions and sausage.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together peanut butter, cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix well and put into crust.
Chill overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan on bottom and sides.
Freeze until set.
Add ice cream and freeze. (May use vanilla or peanut butter ice cream.)
Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve and drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Boil sugar and water until it threads.
Pour syrup into beaten whites.
Beat until cool.
Then add beaten yolks.
Add sifted flour and cream of tartar and salt.
Pour batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma clancy's sin
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo until crumbly.
Spread on bottom of cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until slightly brown.
Blend cream cheese with 1 cup Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread on crust. Mix milk and instant pudding.
Pour on top of cream cheese layer. Chill 2 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip and more pecans.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Thaw the spinach and squeeze most of the water out.
Drain the artichoke hearts and cut into small pieces.
Saute the garlic in the butter for a few minutes.
Break up the spinach into small pieces and drop into the butter-garlic mixture.
Saute mixture for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add artichoke hearts and saute for another 5 minutes.
Add cream and saute for 3 to 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in approximately half of the cheese.
Place mixture into a shallow baking dish (8 to 9-inch pie pan works well) and spread out evenly.
Top with remaining cheese and put in a 350° oven until top cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips and salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish and add seasonings to your taste.
Add mushroom soup (which you follow directions on can to mix up) over top of chicken legs.
Bake at 375° (gas stove) for 1 hour.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend about 30 seconds. Makes 3 cup serving.

title: anise cookies(cake)
directions: Roll out 1/2 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Let stand, uncovered, 12 hours or at least overnight.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Yields 3 dozen 3-inch cookies or 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick spray coating. Saute mushrooms, onion and chicken pieces on all sides over medium heat about 15 minutes. Stir in broth, water and seasonings and transfer to crock-pot. Cook on low. When these ingredients are hot, add rice. Cook until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Chill until firm.

title: lazy daisy frosting
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and milk.
Add coconut and nuts. Spread over hot baked cake.
Place in broiler until brown and bubbly.
Watch closely.

title: ham 'n cheddar cheese casserole
directions: Combine eggs, milk, mustard, onion and Tabasco; mix well. Stir in ham, cheese and crackers. Pour into baking dish and set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Transfer to mixing bowl.
Beat with sugar, until fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in corn syrup, bourbon, molasses, and salt.
Fold in pecans. Pour batter into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes, or until set.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
In separate bowl, blend together thoroughly baking powder and flour.
Slowly add milk to first mixture.
Fold in flour mixture with vanilla.
Add walnuts. Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, glaze or sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1/4 teaspoon sugar. In a small, heavy saucepan, combine the coffee, oil, chocolate and molasses.
Simmer, stirring over low heat until the chocolate is completely melted.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the melted chocolate and coffee mixture with the dissolved yeast.
Stir in the salt and rye flour and mix with an electric mixer.
Gradually beat in the unbleached flour, adding no more than 1 cup at a time to make a workable dough.
Remove the dough to a lightly floured surface and knead for about 10 minutes, adding additional unbleached flour as necessary, until dough is smooth and elastic.
The dough will feel very heavy.

title: not so messy s'mores
directions: Spread peanut butter on graham cracker.
Spread marshmallow creme on another graham cracker.
Put chocolate chips in the middle and stick them together.
Put on paper plate.
Heat in microwave for 10 to 15 seconds.
Get napkin and eat!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion very thinly and sprinkle with salt. Let stand for 1/2 hour, then place in cheesecloth and squeeze out water.
Pour mixture in dish.
Add vinegar and mix.
Pour in sour cream and mix gently.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: jake's favorite brownies
