directions: Melt Crisco and cocoa in saucepan or microwave.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, sugar, and vanilla, then pour Crisco and cocoa mixture into the bowl.
Mix at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix until all ingredients are mixed well.
Pour in greased 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green beans with tomato sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beans, tomato sauce, sugar, salt, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat.
Drain grease. Put meat in long casserole dish.
Combine the 2 soups and pour over the hamburger meat.
Make a layer of Tater Tots.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes (until Tater Tots are done).

title: maureen mcgrail's "chicago" corn chowder
directions: "Wilt" bacon; add butter to melt.
Add onions and "wilt" on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir and cook another 5 minutes.
Add stock and potatoes.
Cook over low heat for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add half and half, corn, pepper and salt (dash).
Cook 7 minutes.
Add bell pepper and scallions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve and garnish with cilantro.

title: french fish soup
directions: Rinse and dry the fish head and bones.
Sprinkle them with salt and pepper and flour and set aside.
In a heavy, 4 to 5-quart pan, heat the olive oil and saute the onions.
Then add the fish head and bones and cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the potatoes, tomatoes, thyme and lemon juice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add more water and the wine.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: out of this world rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine eggs, shortening, sugar, yeast mixture, remaining warm water, salt and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape rolls three hours before baking.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen rolls.

title: elephant soup
directions: Mix 1 1/2 ounces rum with Coke; drink. Wash and dry elephant (don't use shampoo as this will spoil flavor).

Chop into bite-size chunks. In back of 1 ton truck and trailer, pour hot water. Immediately seal all cracks to prevent leaks. Have another rum and Coke; add elephant, potatoes and other ingredients. Allow to simmer.

title: cheese gnocchi
directions: Beat eggs, Ricotta cheese and grated cheese.
Add salt. Gradually add flour.
Knead.
Cut into small pieces; boil in salted boiling water (about 4 quarts).
Can cover with favorite red sauce or serve with butter and grated cheese.
Boil for 20 minutes; drain.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add water, onion and bouillon.
Bring to a boil. Add broccoli and noodles. Boil until noodles are tender.
Add cheese and milk. Let simmer.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie shell with fresh berries.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add strawberry jello and cook until dissolved.
Cool a little and then pour over berries.
Attractive and tasty!

title: winter peach pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie crust shell with peaches.
Cream together sugar, flour, butter and lemon juice.
Add egg, cinnamon and juice drained from peaches.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 10 minutes at 475°, then 50 minutes at 325°.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs with mixer about 30 seconds.
Add margarine. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: prize grilled hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape mixture into patties. Grill for 5 minutes on each side, turning once.
Serve on hot toasted buns.

title: apple puff pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In blender, mix eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Melt butter in a 12-inch quiche dish or a 13 x 9-inch baking dish in the oven.
Add apple slices to baking dish.
Return to oven until butter sizzles; do not let brown.
Remove baking dish from oven and immediately pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in middle of oven for 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon angel cake dessert
directions: Make pudding as directed with 1 egg yolk per box.
Let cool 2 minutes.
Mix jello with the hot water and stir into pudding. Break cake into pieces in cake pan.
Pour mixture over cake. Refrigerate.
Spread Cool Whip over top after has set.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, onions, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown and cool meatballs.
Remove meatballs and keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix well Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add coconut, nuts, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: apricot muffins
directions: Soak apricots in water for 5 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients, stir into creamed mixture just until moistened.
Drain apricots, discarding liquid.
Fold apricots, orange peel and nuts into batter.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons milk in medium microwaveable bowl on high for 45 seconds.
Stir.
(Marshmallows will be partially melted.)
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip.

title: savory stew
directions: Brown
beef in
oil.
Add
everything,
but
carrots, potatoes, celery, lima beans and corn.
Bake
at
350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add rest of the ingredients and continue baking at 350° for 1 hour more.
Serves 20.

title: boiled cake
directions: Boil together raisins, sugar, water and shortening.
Let cool. Add soda, cloves, nutmeg, salt and flour.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add other ingredients and heat through and through.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
When meat begins to turn color, add onion and green pepper.
Saute until meat is well browned.
Combine tamales, kidney beans, corn, tomato sauce, noodles, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and meat mixture in large 3-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yeast waffles
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add yeast and eggs; beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise until light and bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Prepare jello and let set up.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; set aside.
Grind cranberries; add sugar and bring to boiling.
Cool and add jello when slightly thickened.
Pour into mold or pan.
Chill.

title: lemon sour cream frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt, sour cream, lemon juice and peel.
Beat until light and fluffy.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop hearts.
Combine all ingredients in an ungreased casserole, saving a little cheese and crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and next 3 ingredients. Saute until tender.
Stir in beans and next 5 ingredients. Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often.
Place hot rice in 1-quart casserole. Spoon bean mixture over rice. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, pepper and onion.
Toss lightly.
Place in an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add drained kidney beans and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Toss lettuce, onion, tomatoes, grated cheese, avocado and Thousand Island dressing in bowl.
Add ground beef mixture to salad; toss.
Add Doritos.
(Chili may be added.)

title: calypso pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and combine with melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 minutes. When cooled, cover with 1/2 gallon ice cream and freeze.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy raisin icing
directions: Melt shortening; remove from heat.
Blend in flour and salt. Slowly add milk.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add slowly the powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add raisins. Beat until thick enough to spread.
Add cherries and nuts.
A good icing for spice layer cake.

title: taco salad
directions: In medium skillet brown beef; drain off excess fat.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over meat; stir in 3/4 cup water.
Simmer mixture, uncovered, till water cooks away, about 10 minutes.
Stir in hot pepper sauce.
Meanwhile, in salad bowl combine lettuce, cheese, tomato, olives, and green pepper; toss well.
Divide lettuce mixture onto individual salad plates, if desired.
Spoon meat mixture over lettuce; garnish with corn chips.
Pass taco sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baumkuchen-torte(tree cake)
directions: Cream butter with egg yolks and sugar.
Add sifted flour and baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line bottom of a round cake pan with greased wax paper.
Bake the dough in 12 to 15 separate layers (approximately 3 tablespoons at a time) at 350° for 5 minutes, until slightly golden on top.
As each layer cools, brush with apricot jam and put on top of each other.
When finished, cover with chocolate frosting.
Entire baking time is about 1 hour.

title: easy german stew
directions: Chop vegetables into chunks.
Arrange in crock-pot in order listed.
Add a little water, if necessary.
Cook on high for 3 or 4 hours or all day on low (until potatoes are done).
This smells sooo good while cooking and serves 4 generously.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: noodle soup dumplings
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat egg and combine with margarine, bread crumbs and marrow (if desired).
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 1/2-inch balls.
Prepare your favorite noodle soup.
Ten minutes before noodles are tender, add dumplings and continue cooking at medium heat.
Dumplings will increase in size slightly.

title: quick supper
directions: Remove wrappers from tamales and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour chili on top.
Cook in microwave for 4 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to microwave for 20 to 30 seconds.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients well in saucepan; stir in vinegar and water.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Add beets.
Return to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Chill liquid 8 hours before serving.
Cover, store in liquid, chilled, up to one month. Drain before serving.

title: spaghetti carbonara(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute until crisp, bacon, diced.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of the fat.
Add to the pan, chopped green pepper and chopped onions.
Cook slowly until the vegetables are tender. Cook spaghetti in a large kettle.
Drain and rinse the spaghetti. Put in the kettle and keep it warm.
Add eggs and Parmesan cheese (or to taste); stir well.
Reheat the bacon and vegetables and stir them into the spaghetti.
Reheat and serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wedding mints
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix in the powdered sugar. This will become very stiff, use your hands. Add the flavoring.
Colors may be added, but be cautious; pastels are best, so add only 1 drop at a time!
These may be rolled into "logs" and sliced, but are much prettier if molded in tiny candy molds and refrigerated.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate meat overnight.

title: barnie arnold apple pie
directions: Fill pie crust about an inch or two over edge of pie pan with apples.
Mix the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust and slit for steam.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until crust looks done (golden).

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into a loaf pan.
Brush a little cocktail sauce on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or for 25 minutes in a microwave.

title: stuffed mirlitons
directions: Peel mirlitons and boil until tender.
Save some of the water. Put vegetables in pot and cook to clear in oil.
Add ham and saute.
Put cooked mirlitons in pot and cook for about 1 hour slowly.
Put shrimp in pot and cook until shrimp turn pink.
Add some of the mirliton water to pot and then cook for 1/2 hour.
Add enough bread crumbs to make stuffing stiff.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 stick butter and stir well.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook in oven at 250° to 300° until hot.

title: red, white & blue layer salad
directions: Bottom Layer: Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water, cool. Add pineapple; pour into bottom of mold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Stir in pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: waldorf astor cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add food coloring and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) round pans.

title: texas hash (diabetic)
directions: Brown the beef.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, mushrooms and seasonings; cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and rice; heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine the cheeses and sprinkle half over the buttered pan. Break the eggs on top of the cheese.
Poke yolks, but do not stir. Sprinkle with the salt and pepper to taste.
Top with the sausage and mushrooms.
Pour the half and half over.
Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle with paprika or parsley (if desired).
Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 15 servings.

title: petrified sauerkraut
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, in glass dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday fruit bread
directions: Put nuts, dates, fruit, butter and soda in a bowl. Add boiling water. Beat eggs. Add sugar, then flour and salt sifted together. Combine mixture and pour into a buttered loaf pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until cake tests done. Turn from pan to cool. Frost top.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1 cup pecans.
Form into 2 logs and roll in the cup of pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: dilly bread(this recipe has been handed down from bruce's family.)
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine the next 8 ingredients with the yeast.
Add flour (a cup at a time) and mix to form a stiff dough, beating after each addition.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Let rise in warm place 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar, then cream in vanilla, egg yolks, cold water and pureed tomatoes, in that order.
Sift together dry ingredients; mix into creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until they are stiff, then fold into batter.
Bake in two greased and floured 8 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with a chocolate butter frosting.
Top with strawberries.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix well and spread into a 9 x 13 pan (spray with Pam). Sprinkle 1/4 cup Cheddar and 1/4 cup Monterey Jack.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper in hot saucepan with black pepper and red pepper.
After brown, pour in tomato sauce and water.
Add brown sugar, parsley, chili powder or steak and burger seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow all cheeses to get soft.
Mix all ingredients together, except nuts, with hands.
Roll or shape into ball or log.
Roll in nuts and sprinkle with paprika.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and melted butter.
Put 1/3 oysters in buttered casserole, top with layer of cracker crumb mixture.
Repeat, saving some crumb mixture for top.
Pour the milk over contents, top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Bake in 12 baking cups at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box in an oblong pan. While cake is till warm, punch holes in cake with large prong fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut; pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and then coconut; refrigerate.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Roll in balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Combine all in double boiler and bring to a boil.
Serve with chunks of French bread.

title: lime delight(congealed salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: edible menorah(easy for children to make)
directions: Place bread on a plate and flatten with crust.
Spread it with peanut butter.
Stick the carrots onto the peanut butter as bases for the candles.
(Place one higher for the Shammos.)
Stick the pretzels flat on the peanut butter to be candles.
Use the raisins for flames.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and everything else.
Heat on top of stove until thick or it comes to boil. Pour in greased baking dish (8 to 12-inch). Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Combine butter and chocolate in small bowl of mixer.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Add sugar alternately with sour cream and vanilla.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thickened.
Blend Eagle Brand milk with pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line dish with graham crackers.
Layer with 1/3 pudding, bananas and graham crackers. Repeat layers.
End with the pudding.
Crumble graham crackers on top.

title: creamy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cube potatoes and cook until done. Place in the large electric mixer bowl and mash. Add all other ingredients, except cheese, and blend until smooth on medium-high speed. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch casserole dish. Cover and bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Uncover and sprinkle with cheese. Bake another 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wonderland coffee cake
directions: Mix and pour over warm cake if desired.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place kraut on chicken.
Top with cheese.
Pour dressing over next.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until done and almost completely dry.
Add margarine and milk; salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. The starch from the potatoes should be enough thickening.

title: joyce's spumoni
directions: Soften ice cream. Toast almonds under broiler (take care not to burn). Crush macaroon cookies. Chop maraschino cherries. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl (ice cream, almonds, cookies, Cool Whip and cherries).
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan or pour into individual serving containers.
Cover securely and freeze.
When ready to serve, sprinkle toasted almonds and top with cherries.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer.
In separate bowl, mix Ricotta cheese and eggs.
Stir well until creamy.
Place a layer of noodles in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour half of meat sauce over noodles.
Pour half of Ricotta cheese mixture over this.
Sprinkle with half of Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Pour rest of meat sauce over another layer of noodles.
Layer as before using rest of everything.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is lightly brown.
Let set 30 minutes before serving.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mince green pepper, onion and garlic.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add minced mixture to butter or margarine and cook 15 minutes, stirring, remove from heat.
Add lemon juice. Add clams (liquid of only 2 cans).
Add bread crumbs slowly and mix.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with your favorite crackers.

title: kid's banana bread
directions: Mix in first bowl the oil, sugar and egg whites.
Sift in second bowl the flour.
"Mush" on plate the bananas.
Alternate flour and bananas to first bowl.
Mix with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: Coarsely break the Saltines into a bowl.
Add 1 hard cooked egg, chopped, 1 tomato, chopped, 3 green onions, chopped and salt and pepper to taste.
Add Mayonnaise to moisten.

title: country steak
directions: Pound the steak and cut it into serving-size pieces.
In a skillet, brown the meat in the oil; drain.
Combine the soup and water and pour over the meat.
Cover and simmer 1-1/2 hours or until meat is cooked through.
Stir often.
Serves 4-6.

title: strawberry sparkle punch
directions: Put strawberries in blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed until fruit is pureed.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in lemonade concentrate until melted.
Add the cold water, cranberry juice and the strawberry puree.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled ginger ale.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour together.
Stir until smooth. Then add flour to mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Pour mixture into greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake in pre-heated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: frozen whiskey sours
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze and store.
For a drink, spoon some into a blender.
Switch on, then off.
Serve in champagne glasses with straws.
Enough for 8 drinks.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Recommended nuts:
Cashews, peanuts, whole almonds or pecan halves.

title: pretzel pandemonium
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and egg.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Chill. Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries. Chill until partly set.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Combine bacon, broccoli and onions in a salad bowl.
Add raisins.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli.
Mix in sunflower seeds.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt oleo in big pan; add all ingredients except pecans and stir well.
Mix in pecans and stir well.
Cook in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, heat thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together; sprinkle Old Bay on top.
Bake in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes or at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
To serve, add 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup of hot water.

title: watermelon pickle
directions: Peel and slice rind in small pieces.
Cover with cold water. Let stand in cool place for 24 hours.
Rinse thoroughly, then drain well.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes, then drain.
Rinse thoroughly, then drain completely. Bring vinegar, sugar and oils to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved; pour over rind in large kettle.
Stir well until all rind is covered.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Boil for 7 to 10 minutes or until rind is tender.
Pour into crock; stir each day for 5 days.
Return to kettle; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: raspberry and champagne sherbet
directions: Press raspberries through a sieve or food mill; set puree aside and discard seeds.

title: pasta salad #2
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Refrigerate until chilled. Serves 6 to 8.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cheese and beat, add sugar and salt, then the eggs, beating after each egg.
Add vanilla and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and add topping (cool a few minutes first).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Melt cheese, butter and milk in a double broiler.
Crush crackers.
Butter sides of a small casserole.
Alternate in layers:
broccoli, liquid mixture and crackers.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiders
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels, stirring continually.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon. Let cool.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: smokey cheese dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk until smooth.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add bacon bits and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef with chopped onion; salt and pepper to taste. Place over shredded cabbage in casserole dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup boiling water; stir in undiluted mushroom soup. Pour mixture over beef and cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: layered vegetable casserole
directions: In
a
large
glass
casserole dish start with carrots, layer vegetables,
making 2 layers of onion with salt, pepper and butter
between each layer of vegetables.
End with tomatoes on top.
Do not add any liquid.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla in large bowl until blended. Add sugar gradually until well blended.

title: aunt pennie's sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel off skins while still hot. Mash potatoes with fork and add butter and brown sugar.
Mix well. Add Karo syrup and cinnamon to taste.
Put in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and add miniature marshmallows on top.
Place back in oven to brown top of marshmallows.
Delicious.

title: dijon mustard dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a food processor or blender. Process until smooth. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: In large skillet cook diced bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain.

title: oven ham omelette
directions: Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Tear ham in small pieces.
Add cheese and onion.
Stir lightly.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put cooked and drained broccoli in casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grate or crush the Oreo cookies in blender or with rolling pin until fine, 8 to 10 cookies at a time.
Set aside after crushing all cookies. Blend cream cheese, sugar and margarine together in separate bowl.

title: ooey-gooey butter cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and eggs and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over top and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with the 1 Tbsp. sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and curry powder. Mix well.
Place broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Place chicken on top of broccoli. Pour soup mixture over chicken. Spread cheese evenly over sauce. Combine melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine and add together.
Add spices, consomme and juices.
Chill 24 hours and serve with slice of cucumber and 1/2 teaspoon sour cream for garnish.

title: rosy glow cranberry punch(serves 24 half cup servings)
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients; blend well. Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes or until warm.
If desired, remove cinnamon sticks and nutmeg.
Serve warm in mugs or cups. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli, covered, in small amount of boiling water for 15 minutes.
Melt margarine; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth; cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add mushrooms and add a dash of pepper.
Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Drizzle with half the mushroom sauce.
Arrange broccoli on top of the sauce and pour on remaining sauce.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, brown hamburg with onions. Cut cabbage in wedges and add to hamburg and onions.
Pour a large jar of Ragu sauce over cabbage.
Let cook until cabbage is tender. Sprinkle 8 ounces of Mozzarella cheese over cabbage about 10 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk, and cocoa well.
Microwave for 4-6 minutes, stirring half way through.
Add 2 c. oats, 1 c. peanut butter, and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie shell for 10 to 15 minutes; reduce oven setting to 350°.
Combine sugar and flour.
Mix well the eggs, butter, syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix this together and spread in a 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: skillet hamburger upside-down pie
directions: Brown beef, celery, onion and green pepper in shortening until tender.
Stir in salt and soup.
Combine biscuit mix and milk. Roll in circle 1-inch smaller than skillet.
Top meat with dough. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter and top with cheese.

title: poultry pyramids
directions: Blend melted margarine and cream cheese until smooth.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforations.
Stretch to square.
Mix margarine and cream cheese mixture with chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Place 1/4 of mixture on each square.
Pull up all 4 corners of rolls and seal on all edges.
Brush top with melted butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spiced russian tea
directions: May also add 1 package presweetened lemonade mix.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make sauce from first three ingredients until cheese melts. Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well.
Add sauce to broccoli and bake in casserole for 20 minutes at 350°. Add onions and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: squash medley
directions: Cook squash just until tender and drain.
Saute onions in 1 stick of butter.
Take onions out of pan with a slotted spoon and save butter.
Using the butter from the onions, lightly brown the bread crumbs.
Combine squash, onions, tomatoes and cheese in a casserole dish.
Mix gently together.
Top with browned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until cheese is bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: salt map
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add water.
Bring to a slow boil. Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Divide and add food coloring to as many portions as needed for showing different countries or states in a variety of colors.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, margarine and one egg.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Clean beaters and mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over crust. Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt, lemon pepper and oregano.
Place chops 4 to 5 inches from coals.
Grill over low to medium hot coals 25 minutes or until the chops are no longer pink, turning once. Yields 4 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Place corn chips in plate.
Put ground beef on chips, followed by cheese, kidney beans, lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
Top with sour cream, cottage cheese or favorite dressing.

title: carriage cake
directions: Boil water and raisins for 5 minutes and let cool.
Add nuts to flour, white sugar and oleo and add dry ingredients to flour. Add
raisns and
flour a
little
at a
time.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased angel food cake pan.
Mix confectioners sugar and orange juice,
enough
to drip down on sides and stripes on top.

title: curry dip
directions: Make this the day before and refrigerate.
Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
This is a great dip for raw vegetables.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until sandwich consistency.
Can add broth to make more juice.
Serve warm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake cookies 5 to 10 minutes.
Let cool for 2 minutes.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll out like biscuit dough. Place on baking sheet and press with communion form. Lacking a form, use the divider from a miniature ice cube tray, or just cut into small pieces with a knife.

title: better than most anything cake
directions: Layer One:
Blend flour and margarine (softened) with electric mixer. Stir in nuts.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Melt butter and saute green peppers and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart covered casserole.
Bake at 357° for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and bake 10 minutes more.
Melt cheddar cheese on top and serve.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; stir frequently (will scorch).
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet in balls, then smash.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli chicken entree
directions: Melt margarine; stir in croutons, coating well in 9 x 13-inch pan.
"Tender quick" cook broccoli; drain and spread over the croutons.
Spread the chicken over the broccoli; combine the lemon juice, curry powder, mayonnaise and soup; spread on top of chicken.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat the milk, Crisco, sugar and salt; add the yeast and dissolve it in the mixture.
Add the flour and knead it a little. Put in a greased pan and let rise until double in size.
Work it down by kneading it, pinch into rolls.
Place on a greased pan and let rise again.
Cook at 400° until done or golden brown.

title: brownies with nuts
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Spread in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter banana snack
directions: Cut banana lengthwise.
Spread with peanut butter.
Cover with mayo mixture and serve.

title: easy rice bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until moisture is absorbed. Serves 6.
Very good reheated.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: creamy slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until time to serve.
This is something that can be fixed the night before. Great with hamburgers!

title: mama's easy apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with water and cinnamon.
Arrange bread strips over apples.
Combine
sugar, egg and butter; mix well.
Pour mixture over bread, covering to all edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Add sugar gradually to eggs; eat until light and fluffy. Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with oil and sour cream.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan. Makes 2 large loaves or 4 small.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Place dough in an airtight container and store in refrigerator.
As needed, spoon into greased muffin tins, and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
No rising time needed!

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Heat refried beans in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Pour over hot beans.
Add (in order) the remaining ingredients.
Heat again in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fresh orange layer cake
directions: Sift together all the dry ingredients into a bowl and add shortening, grated orange rind and 2/3 of the liquid.
Beat for about 2 minutes and add remaining liquid and 2 medium eggs.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with the following.

title: ground beef creole with rice
directions: Forty-five minutes before serving, in 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is browned (about 10 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Spoon off excess fat.
Drain tomato liquid into meat mixture.
Set tomatoes aside.
Add pepper, celery, paprika, salt and pepper to meat mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until vegies are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: six cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries, in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart bowl.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Cut into individual servings.
Garnish each serving with cherry.
Makes 8 servings.

title: herb salad dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and enjoy.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar. Heat other ingredients and add to brown sugar. Cook to soft-ball stage. Cool 5 minutes. Beat with a wooden spoon.

title: onion pie
directions: Crush saltines and mix with enough butter or margarine to make them stick to a pie plate (approximately 6 tablespoons).
Slice onions very thin.
Simmer in 4 tablespoons butter until soft and clear.
Cool.
Mix sour cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add to onions.
Pour mixture into pie plate and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 more minutes.

title: microwave corn casserole
directions: Combine and mix together the muffin mix, oil, corn, eggs, garlic salt and pimiento.
(Omit the pimiento if your children are like mine and complain of bits of "red" in their corn.)
Pour into an ungreased, 8-inch, round microwave-safe dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: hummus with tahini
directions: Drain and puree garbanzos.
Pound salt and garlic together into a smooth paste.
Add to garbanzos.
Mix with tahini.
Add lemon juice and salt to taste.
Place in a serving dish and sprinkle lightly with oil.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Use as dip with crackers or vegetables.

title: schonbrun family corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs until smooth.
Add buttermilk and mix well to blend.
Pour in flour, butter, sugar and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into deep dish pie shell and bake one hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let cool if oily.

title: snickers salad
directions: Cut up apples and Snickers bars.
Mix together with Cool Whip.

title: potatoes baked in coals
directions: For moist potatoes, soft skins:
Pierce each potato on 2 sides with fork.
Nest in a square of heavy-duty foil.
Add 1 teaspoon water.
Wrap tightly and bury in coals.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Drain fat.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wilted spinach vinaigrette
directions: Remove stems from spinach leaves with kitchen shears.
Wash and blot dry.
In frypan, saute garlic in oil for 1 minute.
Add spinach and raisins.
Stir constantly until spinach is barely wilted, about 1 minute 15 seconds.
Add seeds and vinegar.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 30 minutes at 350°. Mix the next 4 ingredients and frost the cake. Sprinkle 1 can of Angel Flake coconut over frosted cake.

title: frosted chewies
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup over medium heat until it boils. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Special K and stir.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool. Melt both chips together.
Remove from heat and spread over Special K mixture.
Cool until firm.

title: dieter's dip
directions: Place all in a blender.
Blend well.
Chill overnight.
Use with your choice of fresh veggies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in at least a 3-quart cooker.
Add sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Cook on stove at medium heat.
When it starts to boil, time for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
Take off of heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly, then add oats.
Stir until oats are coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper or aluminum foil.
Cool before serving.

title: marinated fresh mushrooms
directions: Wash, dry and slice mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until all mushrooms are coated with spices.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Refrigerate.
Serve as party snack.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Boil pasta and butter according to package directions. Fry hamburger with onion and green pepper. Drain and add mushrooms and add the spaghetti sauce. Drain and rinse cooked pasta. In a 9 x 9 dish, put a layer of pasta, a layer of meat sauce and a layer of cheeses. Sprinkle a layer of Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers once more.

title: goldfish snack
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large Ziploc bag or mixing bowl. Enjoy munching!
Note:
Leave off the popped corn for a different taste.

title: cereal candy
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and nuts.
Slowly melt coating.
Oil in double boiler.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Add marshmallows when it is well mixed so they won't melt.
Mix well. Spread on waxed paper.
Let dry and break into pieces.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix oil, pudding and sour cream.
Add cake mix and eggs; beat for 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour half of this in greased tube pan.
Put half of the chocolate chips and nuts on top. Add remainder of batter and top with remainder of chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy pecan caramel rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 8 x 8 x 2-inch round pan, add margarine and sugar.
Heat until melted, then add pecans in even layer. Separate biscuits and roll the sides of each in cinnamon.
Place biscuits in pan, covering pecans.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert pan on plate.
Will be hot and juicy.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add water and mix as for pie crust.
Place dough into King cookie press tube and use any of the following forms:
small or large star, bar or small circle. Form dough in long lines on cookie sheet and cut into desired lengths with sharp knife.
Separate slightly.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes deluxe
directions: Peel and boil potatoes as usual.
Mash with salt, pepper and small amount of milk.
Add sour cream, cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Mash all together and put in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes at 300° (longer if potatoes come directly from refrigerator).

title: saturday night spread
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve on white toast or hamburger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring to boil the lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Dissolve jello in cold water.
Mix all of this and partly chill.
Then add whipped whipping cream, cheese and nuts.
Chill until set, then serve.

title: seasoned italian bread
directions: Slice loaf lengthwise. Drizzle generously with olive oil. Add generous amount of pepper over oil. Cover with a thin layer of cheese. Wrap in foil and heat for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve with vegetable, lentil, or minestrone soup.

title: rice delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in a microwave on High until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir occasionally.

title: chili con carne * chow mein noodles
directions: Melt fat in heavy skillet over low heat, add onions, peppers and garlic; stir gently about 3 minutes, or until soft and slightly brown. Remove garlic; add remaining ingredients.

title: gladys' cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Cook only until edges start to brown.

title: sugar cookies(a christmas tradition)
directions: Let butter soften.
Cream butter.
Add sugar, egg, baking powder and salt.
Add flour and sufficient milk to make a stiff dough.
Chill.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or less. These burn easily.

title: white sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice in 2 large pitchers.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve over ice.

title: rotini lasagna
directions: Mix together Ricotta cheese, egg whites, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil and peel potatoes.
Slice and put in Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.

title: dill dip for "veggies"
directions: Stir all ingredients together and serve with vegetables for dipping.

title: lamb stew
directions: Coat meat with flour.
In a large saucepan, brown meat in a small amount of hot shortening.
Add 3 cups water, garlic, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until meat is almost tender.
Add carrots, onions, potatoes and basil; cook, uncovered, 20 minutes or until done.
Add peas and parsley.
Cook 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix all except cheese and tortillas.
Dip tortillas in hot chicken broth to soften, then place layer in buttered casserole dish.
Place layer of chicken mixture on tortillas, then put layer of cheese.
Continue to layer, ending with tortilla then cheese. Add some broth if needed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork skillet
directions: Brown pork in cooking oil in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add liquid, vinegar, salt, garlic salt and sugar to pork; stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and stir in rice.
Cover and continue cooking about 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and pork is tender.
Stir in pineapple tidbits, green pepper and tomato wedges.
Heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave rice
directions: Wash rice.
Place in a tall glass bowl with lid.
Add water. Place 3 paper towels between bowl and lid to absorb water.
Place in microwave for 15 minutes on High.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: zippy nachos
directions: On a 10-inch paper plate or glass plate with wax paper, arrange tortilla chips evenly on plate.
Place small slice of jalapeno pepper on each chip and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Microwave for 3 to 8 minutes, rotating plate once or twice.

title: tempting taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning mix.
Cool and drain. Mix in large bowl the lettuce, tomato, onion, cheese and prepared taco meat.
Add chips and toss with dressing just before serving.

title: zia peppina's anise toast cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and flavoring and mix to form dough.
Shape into 4 loaves and bake in 350° oven about 1/2 hour.
Cool and slice on the diagonal.
Place on cookie tray, cut side down, and return to oven to dry out and brown.
Turn over if necessary.

title: tom and jerry batter
directions: Beat whites until very stiff.
In separate bowl, beat yolks 10 minutes.
Mix whites and yolks together and beat very well.
Add flour and beat very, very well.
Add powdered sugar and beat 15 minutes.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring well until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt, pepper and peas.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: fiesta biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine flour, cheese, chilies, and whipping cream in bowl of food processor.
Process until mixture forms a dough.
Remove onto a lightly floured surface and knead 5 or 6 times.
Roll to a thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter.
Combine the melted butter and taco seasoning.
Dip each biscuit into butter mixture and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 small biscuits.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide
nuts and chips evenly into the bottoms of the 2 pie shells.
Mix thoroughly the butter, eggs, sugar and syrup and divide
between the pie shells.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy seafood pasta
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add flour, salt and milk; microwave on High, stirring every 2 minutes until thickened.
Add cheese.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, 1 cup sugar, egg and molasses.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients (flour, soda, cinnamon and ginger) and then stir them into shortening mixture.
Form dough into small walnut-sized balls and dip tops into dish of water and then in 1/4 cup sugar.
Place sugar side up on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Cookies will flatten as they bake.

title: barbecue sauce for hamburgers
directions: Boil 15 minutes.
Add more water if necessary.
Pour over meat and bake.

title: cranberry sauce jello salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce until it bubbles.
Take off heat and add jello; mix.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Put in a 10 x 7 x 2-inch pan and let set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce or watercress.
Top with cream dressing.
Can be made ahead.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add oil. Place skillet over medium high heat until hot.
Add chicken. Cook 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drain chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.

title: sweet 'n sour spread
directions: Combine pineapple preserves, horseradish and mustard; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spoon pineapple mixture over softened cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream the peanut butter and margarine.
Add vanilla and sugar until mixture reaches consistency of balls.
Form small balls with hands.
Melt 1/2 cake Candy Quick and 1 package chocolate chips. Dip balls into chocolate mixture; place on waxed paper until cool. Use toothpicks to dip with.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Cool and ice with mocha or buttercream icing.

title: basic sliced cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.

Add about half of the flour, the sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, baking soda and salt to the shortening mixture. Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally, then beat or stir in the remaining flour.

title: ever crisp onion rings
directions: Mix; let stand at least 3 hours at room temperature.
Line jelly roll pan with layers of brown paper bags and top with paper towels.
Cut sweet onions (Vidalia best) into 1/4-inch thick rings.
Heat oil or solid Crisco to 375° (about 2-inches deep in deep pan).
Dip rings in batter and fry to golden brown. (Chopsticks work great for turning and removing from hot oil.) Place on lined pan and place in middle rack in a 200° oven.
Will stay crisp at least 2 hours.

title: all-purpose salad dressing
directions: In small bowl, whisk together wine, vinegar and mustard until blended.
Slowly pour in olive oil, whisking constantly.
Whisk in oregano, parsley and garlic.
Use for dressing on mixed greens. Yield:
3/4 cup.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken, into strips. Stir in minced garlic and a small amount of hot oil. Cook on mid-high heat until chicken is cooked through. Add water, stir-fry, soy sauce and sugar, stir. Bring to rolling boil. Stir in rice, cover. Remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes, before serving.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: Cook the onion in hot oil in a medium saucepan until tender, but not brown.
Add carrots, chicken or vegetable broth, water and desired herb or spice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Pour half of carrot mixture in a blender container.
Cover; blend until the mixture is smooth.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Return to saucepan.
Add milk.
Cook until heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
To garnish, swirl a dollop of sour cream atop each serving of soup, if desired.

title: the bible cake
directions: Mix well and bake in well-greased and floured tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes).

title: peach cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Serve plain or with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin crunch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sift yellow cake mix on top. Sprinkle with pecans.
Drizzle 1/2 stick margarine on top.
Cook in long Pyrex dish.
Bake about 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil water, oleo and cocoa until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: quick cherry crunch
directions: Mix cherry juice and tapioca and let stand 15 minutes.
Melt butter in large pan, then mix with it brown sugar, flour, oatmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Scatter over it drained cherries, and the juice and tapioca mixture.
Cover the fruit with the other half of the pastry mixture.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together in top of double boiler. Add slowly to the mixture the coconut and milk.
Cook over boiling water 15 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: sausage squares
directions: Mix biscuit mix and milk.
Add mayonnaise.
Put in well-greased casserole and pat down.
Saute the sausage and onion. Drain real well.
Squeeze out.
Spread in layer on top of biscuit mixture.
Add egg and mayonnaise mixture with grated cheese and green chilies.
Pour over top and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°. Cut in squares at cocktail parties.

title: boarding house bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, the yeast, parsley flakes, celery flakes, thyme and basil.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, oil and salts just until warm (115° to 120°).
Add to dry mixture in mixing bowl; add whole egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth, 5 to 8 minutes.
Shape into a ball.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Bake at 250°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Pick off the bone and cut into small pieces.
Return meat to broth that chicken was cooked in.
May need to add more water.
Chop the celery and onion until fine.
Add to meat and broth.
Also add bouillon cube and butter. Let simmer 15 minutes, then add rice.
Turn off and cover for 5 minutes.
Can simmer longer, if needed.

title: broccoli enchilada
directions: Cut broccoli into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in saucepan with sauce.
Cover and let simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt cheese on tortilla and put 3 to 4 tablespoons broccoli in middle.
Top with your favorite enchilada ingredients (sour cream, salsa, olives, etc.).

title: low calorie pineapple cheesecake
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar in saucepan; beat egg yolks and milk together.
Stir in to gelatin mixture.
Place over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly. Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and sweetener.
Beat cottage cheese on high speed until smooth and creamy.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Stir occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites, pinch of salt and cream of tartar until soft but firm peaks form.
Fold into gelatin-cheese mixture.
Fold in pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping gradually.
Pour into crusts.
Chill several hours. Yields about 16 servings, 130 calories per serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir in 3 cups of milk and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir part of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Boil 2 minutes longer, stirring. Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup of butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Taste to check salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fondue(tater's own)
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Cut up Velveeta cheese in blocks.
Add cheese, beans and picante sauce along with hamburger in microwave safe dish.
Microwave until cheese is melted, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: yellow cake with peanut butter filling
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on package and bake; cool.
Mix all ingredients except peanut butter in skillet and cook until mixture forms a soft ball, about 25 minutes.
Then add peanut butter and beat until cool enough to spread on cake. Frost cake and decorate top with roasted peanuts.

title: apple dumplin
directions: Roll out biscuits one at a time.
Put heaping tablespoon of apples in each biscuit.
Bring sides up and pinch together.
Bring margarine, sugar, cinnamon and 7-Up to a boil.
Pour over dumplins. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion, soup, tomatoes and juices, chili powder and beans.
Cover and simmer until onions are done.

title: meatballs(makes 75 meatballs)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and form into very small balls. Fry until well done.
Drain.
Cover with sauce made from last 3 ingredients.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place the ingredients in layers in order: pineapple, pie filling, sugar, cake mix and margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until liquid is absorbed.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and arrange slices on bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Very slowly melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix.
Drop on wax paper and cool. Yields 75.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cut butter into flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt until mixture looks like fine crumbs.
Stir in raisins and enough buttermilk to make a soft dough.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine or butter, stirring constantly for about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Beat until mixture starts to become thick. Pour into desired size pan and cool completely before cutting into whatever size pieces you like.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Combine with mixer the butter, flour and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown. Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over first layer.
It spreads better at room temperature.
Mix both puddings and milk; spread over second layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over third layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on Cool Whip.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack small cucumbers in quart jars and add 1 garlic clove, 1 dill head, 1 pod hot pepper, 1/4 teaspoon alum and 1/4 teaspoon turmeric to each jar.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to a boil and fill jars with hot mixture.
Seal.
Vinegar mixture will make 5 to 6 quarts of pickles.

title: blt sandwiches
directions: This sandwich is especially good on toasted whole wheat bread. If you prefer, it can be made on plain white bread, but it is not as eye-appealing.

title: onion swiss pie
directions: Combine bacon, onion, Swiss cheese, sour cream, eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until a knife comes out clean from center.

title: pizza
directions: Put crust on pan.
Top with tomato sauce.
Add your favorite ingredients; top with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: farm style oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, milk and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Flatten with wet glass.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts or chips, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft.
They'll puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.)
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: golf balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and vanilla; add dry ingredients until completely kneaded.
Shape into golf size or smaller balls. Set aside.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and set on wax paper to dry.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, combine margarine and parsley.
Spread on 1 side of each bread slice.
Place, buttered side down, on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan or cookie sheet.
Toast in 400° oven for 5 minutes, turning at end of 5 minutes.
Cut cheese slices into 4 squares each.
Place 2 slices on top of each bread slice.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more or until melted. Garnish with fresh chopped parsley.
Yields 8 slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add after the above mixture has started to jell.

title: bacon "n" egg spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly in lukewarm water; drain.
Chill to crisp.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine seasonings with flour.
Sprinkle and pound into veal. Heat oil.
Add veal slices and saute over medium heat, four minutes each side, until golden.

title: dr. pepper salad
directions: Add water to Dr. Pepper to
equal 4 cups liquid.
Heat and stir in jello until dissolved.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Add cream cheese and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Chill until firm.
Do not boil Dr. Pepper.

title: apple pie
directions: Melt
butter
and mix with sugar.
Combine orange juice and apples,
pouring into two pie shells.
Lattice top of pies with remaining
pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown.
Turn oven to 300° for another 20 to 30 minutes. Yield:
2 pies.

title: cherry-chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Stir in 1 can cherry pie filling, 1 cup chocolate chips, 1 cup chopped walnuts. Stir with spoon until well mixed. Grease and flour bundt cake pan. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce(july 20, 1975)
directions: You will need 1 large, stainless steel pot.

title: praline and orange sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan stir together sugars, flour and salt.
Stir in 2/3 cup water, orange peel and orange juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Add marshmallows and margarine and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add pecans and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream. Chill leftover sauce to reheat later over a low heat.
Makes 2 cups.

title: "hearty soup"
directions: Saute garlic with chourico in enough olive oil to cover bottom of
pan.
Quart
pan is good.
Add broth, 1 can water, celery, carrots, beans, bay leaves and tomato sauce.
Cook for 20 minutes. Add
cut
up escarole, salt, pepper and a few dry red pepper flakes.
Add cooked rice or orso.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Place chocolate chips, milk and margarine in top of double boiler.
Cook over medium heat until chocolate chips and margarine are melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.

title: graham muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add milk, egg and melted shortening.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef stew deluxe
directions: IT IS NOT NECESSARY TO BROWN MEAT. Mix all ingredients in a covered casserole dish and bake at 300° for 3 hours. Serve over fluffy rice, noodles or whipped potatoes. Thicken gravy if necessary. Raise temperature of over to 400°.
Remove cover from pan and add 1 can of refrigerated canned biscuits to top of stew. Bake until biscuits are browned. Bake extra biscuits to serve stew over biscuit.

title: margaret's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 90 minutes at 350°. Let meat loaf set for a few minutes after cooking. Drain off fat.

title: meat loaf #1
directions: Combine ingredients, shape into loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips and the walnuts.
Spread in an 8-inch square Pyrex dish that has been greased.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips on top.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes, turning dish every 2 minutes, until done.
Cool and cut into bars.
Do not overbake.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck; set aside.
Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove from grease and crumble.
Saute celery and onion in the bacon grease; drain.
Combine all ingredients into a baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, Crisco and buttermilk.
Mix well by hand.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Batter will keep in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Small amounts can be baked fresh as you need them and store batter. Extra dry fruits can be added to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Remove sausage from casing and mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° on each side.

title: pult or klubb
directions: Sift flour, sugar, spices and salt together.
Add liquids and stir well.
Add raisins, rice and suet.
Dough will be soft; pour into greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Place cans in a pan of water and place in bottom of oven.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Cool and freeze or cool and then slice in 1/2-inch slices; fry in butter and serve with syrup.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and tapioca pudding in boiling water.
Stir well.
Let gel but not harden for 2 hours in fridge.
Mix in well drained mandarin oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a deep casserole dish, put a layer of Ritz crackers, then squash, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, bacon bits, cheese and mushroom soup.
Put butter, salt and pepper.
Now, keep layers of squash, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, bacon bits and cheese, almost to the top.
Put a layer of Ritz crackers on top, then spread cream of mushroom soup on top of crackers.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: grandma leaver's zucchini bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Blend eggs, salad oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured oblong glass casserole pan or bread tins.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil until blended.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts and apples.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: marigold cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese, shredded sharp cheese, prepared mustard, Worcestershire sauce and cayenne pepper in mixer bowl until smooth.
Stir in chopped marigold petals.
Shape into ball and roll in marigold petals.
Chill until serving time and garnish with whole marigolds.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine and 2 squares unsweetened chocolate. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and flour; mix well. Spread into greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook ground beef and onions, stirring frequently until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and baking mix in blender on high speed about 15 seconds or with wire whisk or hand beater about 1 minute, until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Combine sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves onto waxed paper.
Add to pumpkin mixture alternating with water; mix until blended.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Heat Coca-Cola to boiling; stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Add black cherries with juice.
Stir until mixed well.
Add pineapple that has been drained and pecans.
You may shred cream cheese and add, or wait until Jell-O salad is set and then mix a little milk, confectioners sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract. Spread this mixture over the top.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets, drain, peel and slice.
(Reserve 1 cup liquid.) Combine liquid, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Tie spice in a bag; add to liquid.
Heat to boiling; add beets.
Simmer 5 minutes. Remove spice bag.
Continue cooking while packing 1 jar at a time. Fill to within 1/2 inch of top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Remove from canner and cool.
Check seals before storing.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off the bone.
In remaining broth, cook noodles and onion.
When noodles are done, drain off any remaining broth.
Add chicken and soup to noodles.
Mix well.
Add at least 1 cup of cheese to the chicken and noodles.
Pour in casserole dish and top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple together and heat until Jell-O is melted.
Cool.
Then add buttermilk and whipped topping and mix well.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix egg, orange juice and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix together and spread 1 heaping spoonful on tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in foil and chill 2 hours.
Cut into slices and serve with picante sauce.
Freezes well.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Heat cream cheese until soft or let soften by self.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Transfer to fondue pot or chafing dish. Garnish with shrimp, if desired.
Serve with your favorite dipper (chips, Triscuits, Dipsy Doodles), also good cold.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas; save juice.
Heat the juice and mushroom soup; add cheese.
Layer asparagus and peas with boiled eggs, pimento and cheese mixture with cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate over night.
Makes 2 casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix milk, corn meal, egg, baking powder, salt and creamed corn together and set aside.
Scramble hamburger until all red is gone. Do not brown (salt to taste).
Heat heavy skillet with small amount of grease, pour 1/2 of butter in skillet.
Sprinkle evenly over batter the meat, onion and peppers and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Pour remaining batter over this and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until browned.
Serve with pinto beans and tossed salad.
Cooked best in iron skillet but can be put in pan and baked in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes

title: domino cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Stir in flour and cocoa. Press dough out to form a 12 x 6-inch rectangle on ungreased cookie sheet.
With knife, score 5 lengthwise lines, 1 inch apart, and 11 crosswise lines, 1 inch apart.
Arrange vanilla chips, flat side up, inside score lines to resemble dots on dominoes.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into rectangles.
Cool 5 minutes more and remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add milk, corn, grated cheese and eggs.
Stir well.
Add onion, peppers and bacon drippings. Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cheese together.
Layer pineapple and then cheese mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs. Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Put vanilla wafer in bottom of mini cupcake holders.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with mixer. Pour into cupcake holders with wafer.
Bake at 300° on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Makes 24.
Top with strawberry slices, pineapple slices or kiwi slices.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Crush chips in bottom of casserole dish to cover bottom.
Add browned taco seasoned hamburger.
In layers, add refried beans, Mexican beans and Ro-Tel.
Add grated cheese to top of this and crush
more chips to cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gram's irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix raisins with sifted flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, sugar and caraway seed.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender (made with 2 knives used scissors fashion) until the consistency of coarse cornmeal.
Gradually add buttermilk and eggs and mix gently until just moistened.
Knead lightly until smooth on a floured board and shape into a round loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, folding chicken in last. Top with 1 cup crushed cornflakes in 3/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup blanched almonds. Bake until brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seven layer garden salad
directions: Fill large bowl half full with broken up lettuce.
Add in layers: onion, green pepper, celery and peas.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over layer of peas.
Do not mix!
Sprinkle sugar and pepper over dressing and cover top with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top of cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Keeps well for several days.

title: mustard dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together with spoon and refrigerate. Great with pretzels.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put rice in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup with water and pour over rice.
Dip chicken breast in melted butter, then lay on top of rice. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine and mix 2 tablespoons with a cup of hot water.
Add sugar to taste.
Can use Sweet 'N Low.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly. Shape into meatballs. Place in glass baking pan. Brown for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple bake
directions: Peel and slice apples. Cover bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Remove crust from bread and cut into strips.
Place over apples. Mix margarine, sugar, flour and egg.
Pour over apples and bread. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: san francisco stroganoff
directions: Shape ground beef into balls.
Brown in butter.
Add 1 sliced onion; cook until tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together fruit; add pudding.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, put rice and milk.
Heat and stir until boiling.
Stir until rice gets thick and creamy.
Turn off burner and stir in salt, sugar, oleo, vanilla and eggs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: original chex mix
directions: Combine salt, Worcestershire and melted margarine.
Mix well. In a plastic bag, combine cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal.
Seal bag and shake well until all pieces are evenly coated.
Cook as follows.

title: basmati rice with peas
directions: Cook basamati rice with basil in rice cooker until done.
When still very hot, add frozen peas, salt and pepper.
Stir very well until frozen peas are warm.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water for about 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine carrot, onion and 1/2 cup water in a large saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes and drain.
Add yogurt and zucchini to saucepan.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients at one time.
Put into 2 loaf pans, 1/4 batter in each of pans.
Then mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Sprinkle on batter, then put rest of batter in loaf pans. Cover with rest of sugar and cinnamon mixture. Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool in loaf pans. Can be cut in slices and put on platter after completely cool.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and pineapple alternately.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Makes a nice cake.

title: old virginia pound cake
