directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: scallop or shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and garlic in olive oil.
When soft, add pepper, thyme, cayenne pepper, bay leaf, brown sugar and salt.
Stir well.
Add tomatoes; cook over low heat 30 minutes or until sauce is thick.
Add mushrooms and celery and cook for a few more minutes.
Add parsley and shrimp or scallops and cook 5 to 10 minutes until shellfish is cooked through.
Serve over rice immediately so that shellfish will not overcook.

title: almond crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased baking sheets.
In a large bowl, blend granulated sugar, powdered sugar, oleo and oil until well mixed. Add almond extract and eggs.
Mix well. Blend dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in almonds and brickle. Chill dough. Shape large tablespoonfuls of dough into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place about 4 to 5-inches apart on baking sheets.
With fork dipped in sugar, flatten cookies in crisscross pattern.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown around the edges. Cool 1 minute before removing from pans to racks.
Makes about 50 cookies.
You can vary size to your wishes.
May need some adjustment in time then.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together until fluffy.
This makes good decorator icing, also.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat together the oil and sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
In a separate bowl combine flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to egg mixture; blend.
Add vanilla and beat together well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn onto cooling rack to continue cooling.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: fennel cookies
directions: Cream butter with electric mixer; add sugar slowly.
Cream well; add eggs, slowly, one at a time, beating well.
Add flavoring and mix 2 minutes longer.
Mix rest by hand.
Add fennel seed.
Now add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Put by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge squares
directions: Combine water, oleo and chocolate in pan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, soda, salt and mix well.
Bake in a jelly roll pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil, debone and cut chicken into small chunks.
(Save broth.) Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.

title: easy-do fudge
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and milk in large heavy saucepan.
Over low heat, bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling for five minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously, making certain all particles are dissolved.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: blender bean soup
directions: Place about 1/3 of the dry beans in a blender container; blend until chopped. Remove; repeat process until all beans are chopped. Place carrots in blender; cover with water.

Blend until coarsely chopped; drain. Combine chopped beans, carrots, 2 quarts water, ham bone, salt, pepper and bay leaf in large kettle. Cover; simmer 3 hours, adding onion the last hour. Remove ham bone and bay leaf. Add about 1/3 of the bean mixture at a time to blender container. Blend at low speed until nearly smooth. Cut ham off bone; add to soup. Serves 8.

title: adobe chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine brown and white rice, tomatoes, onion, and cubed chicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon half of mixture into a shallow, greased 9-inch by 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with half the sour cream, chile strips, cheese and all of the olives.
(This much can be done ahead, covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours.)
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes (1 hour if chilled).
Allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue deer meat
directions: Cook meat until tender along with onion.
Pull meat apart and mix with ingredients.
Put in jars and seal.

title: hearty beef and vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large pot.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until macaroni and vegetables are soft, about 20 minutes.

title: skillet beans
directions: Brown beef and onion, then drain off grease.
Add beans, mustard and ketchup; simmer until hot.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
In casserole, put 1/2 of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with broken Doritos (2 cups), 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese and remaining chicken mixture.
Crush Doritos to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly, uncovered.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add melted margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat sugar and oil for 2 minutes, add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Add grated carrots and vanilla.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy; blend in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop round sized tablespoons of dough 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies and 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: peanut butter pie *
directions: Blend cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend well.
Pour into cooled pie shell and chill.
May be frozen for later use.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Mix well and let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, nuts and vanilla together well; spread over gelatin.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: In small saucepan, place prunes and allspice with 1 cup water. Bring to boil; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Cut orange over medium bowl to catch juices.
Add remaining fruits and prune mixture to bowl and stir gently to mix. Serve at once, or cover and refrigerate.
Makes 10 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix sugar and oil well, then add eggs.
Mix well then add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix until smooth; fold in zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 12 x 16 1/2-inch greased pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and ice with frosting made with:

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil and fry onions and peppers (coarsely chopped) until brown.
Add carrots and cook until tender.
Add eggs, stirred slightly, soy sauce and salt.
Add cooked rice.

title: grapefruit ham roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion and next 3 together. Spread each slice of ham with cream cheese mixture. Place 2 grapefruit sections on 1 end of each ham slice; roll up.
Serve with toothpicks. Cut each roll into fourths. Garnish with sliced olives.

title: pear honey(jam or marmalade)
directions: Boil pears until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Makes 6 pints.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine; pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: bar-b-que saladfort morgan, colorado
directions: Toss cabbage, onions and carrots together.
Heat to a boil the sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery salt.
After it is boiling, add salt, pepper and oil.
Do not stir mixture.
Watch it because it will boil over.
Let set 24 hours.
(You don't have to.)

title: never fail banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs and add with bananas; add with sugar and shortening.
Mix dry sifted ingredients 1/2 at a time into creamed ingredients.
Bake in a greased bread pan for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach in a towel until dry.
Combine soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and spinach; blend well.
Add water chestnuts and scallions; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable tray or crackers.

title: sherri's meatballs
directions: Crumble bread and mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and brown.
Simmer in 4 cans of tomato sauce with mushrooms.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into cubes (leave peeling on, if desired).
Cook potatoes for about 15 minutes, then put them in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a food processor, chop the bacon, cheese and onion together.
Add the mayonnaise and sour cream to this mixture, it will be very thick, then spread this over the potatoes in the pan.
You can retain some of the cheese to sprinkle on top.

title: ann lipscomb's hot spiced cider
directions: Bring all ingredients, except orange juice and lemon juice, to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain
juice from one jar of artichokes into a skillet. Saute onion
and garlic in juice.
Drain second jar;
discard juice. Chop
all
artichokes.
In a bowl beat eggs; add bread crumbs, oregano,
Tabasco,
salt
and pepper.
Stir in onion, garlic, artichokes and cheese; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch pan 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.

title: no peek cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: honey popcorn balls
directions: Combine brown sugar, honey, caramels and butter in a pan over low heat.
Stir a little until mixture bubbles around edge.
Pour over popped corn in a large bowl.
Mix popcorn, nuts and syrup until well blended.
Shape with buttered hands to form balls.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix and spread on crackers.

title: roberta's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand or in a food processor. Form into loaf. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: breaded rigatoni
directions: Cook rigatoni to directions.
Brown bread crumbs (dry in skillet).
Saute garlic, diced, in oil.
Drain rigatoni; mix with oil and garlic, then mix with dry bread crumbs.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, egg, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper by hand.
Press into 9-inch pie pan, forming a shell.
Bake until brown and firm (about 15 minutes).
Remove from oven; pour off fat.
Set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Mix together mashed potatoes, Cheddar cheese and frozen peas and carrots.
Spoon into shell.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over stuffing mix.
Put remaining stuffing mix over squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bryan's daddy's pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, vegetable oil and egg.
Mix in vanilla and applesauce.
Pour on hot griddle.
Flip, serve and enjoy.

title: vegetable-chicken noodle soup
directions: Place 1/3 cup chicken broth, celery, carrots and potatoes with spices in a large saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in remaining broth.
Bring to a boil and add noodles.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Stir in chicken.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer until heated through.
Makes 6 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch in a medium saucepan. Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until filling boils. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling.
Cool; chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: cheese grits
directions: Boil grits, water and salt according to directions on box of grits.
While hot, add butter and cheese.
Beat eggs in a cup and add enough milk to fill cup.
Add to grits.
Bake in a greased casserole for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Knead flour and butter and press in pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over first layer.
Mix pudding and milk well.
Spread on second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: ed's green beans
directions: Pour green beans in a casserole.
Sprinkle with onion powder. Sprinkle brown sugar over beans; pat with 1/4 cup butter and layer with 4 strips bacon.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add in cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic, beating until smooth.
Stir in chives. Spoon into lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate clouds
directions: Line cookie sheets with aluminum foil.
Finely chop baking chocolate in blender and set aside.
Stir together confectioners sugar and cocoa powder with a wire whisk and set aside.
In bowl, beat egg white and cream of tartar with an electric mixer at medium speed until thickens.
Increase to high speed and slowly add white sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold in cocoa mixture and chocolate until mixture is uniformly brown. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Let cookies dry at room temperature for approximately 45 minutes.
Bake at
200° for 1 hour.
Store in airtight container. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: thai noodles with spicy peanut sauce
directions: Cook linguine.	Rinse, drain and toss with olive oil.
Cut veggies into matchsticks or dice. Toss sauce with noodles and vegetables.
Garnish with scallions and sesame seeds.
Can be served hot or cold.
(If serving hot, blanch veggies).

title: tuna and noodle casserole supreme
directions: Cook noodles.
Peel and slice eggs.
Drain tuna.
Arrange layers of noodles, sliced egg, flaked tuna and peas, ending with noodles.
Heat the soup.
Pour over mixture in casserole, pushing gently with fork.
Top with grated cheese and bake in hot oven (375°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey-fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.
Add honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add oil gradually while beating.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: kugelis
directions: Grate potatoes and onions.
For best results, hand grate.
Mix these and remaining ingredients together.
Spread into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°; continue baking for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with sour cream as a side dish with sausage and sauerkraut.

title: imperial crab
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add crabmeat and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into crab shells or small casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil at medium heat about 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: wedding shower cake(1932 applesauce cake)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten egg, spices, flour, applesauce with soda, raisins, vanilla and salt (nuts, if wanted). Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: creole gumbo
directions: In 3-quart saucepan or large Dutch oven, melt butter and stir in flour.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add ham, shrimp, garlic, mushrooms, V-8 juice, okra and shrimp.
Add 8 cups of water and bring mixture to boil for 20 minutes.
Add crab meat, lower heat and simmer for 2 hours. Just before serving, add wine.
Serves 6.

title: lemon butter chicken
directions: Generously salt pieces of chicken on all sides. Use pepper according to taste. Place chicken in shallow baking dishes with bony sides up. Melt butter. Add lemon juice and paprika and pour over chicken. Bake 30 minutes at 425°. Turn; baste and bake 30 minutes longer. Serve with rice. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 5 hours. Delicious.

title: summer fruit crisp
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix fruit with sugar and juice.
Spread in pan.
Put remaining ingredients in a bowl.
With hands, rub to crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly on fruit.
Bake at 375° for 20 or 25 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned on top.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sliced potatoes, onion, pork chops and mushroom soup mixed with water.
Bake until pork chops are done.

title: no-crust strawberry pie
directions: Rinse and slice strawberries. Distribute evenly in 10-inch pie pan.

title: crispy old-fashioned potato pancakes
directions: Make a batter using only the yolk for the moment.
Beat the egg white or whites until they form a peak.
Then fold the beaten egg whites in the batter.
Dip tomatoes in the batter and fry. Serve with smothered onion and green peppers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a bowl. Beat in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt. Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken wings(christmas open house)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight. Place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until lightly brown and crusty.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes	and
cut
in
quarters.
Combine flour, cheese,
salt,
pepper
in plastic bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few times in bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, turning once during baking.

title: swan house salad
directions: Spray Pyrex dish (long one) with Pam.
Cream sugar and softened cream cheese.
Drain strawberries and pineapple.
Fold together with nuts and Cool Whip.
Fold in banana slices last.
Add to sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Turn into Pyrex dish and freeze firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 1 hour, then lower the oven temperature to 200° to 225° and continue cooking (uncovered) for 2 hours.

title: grandma's german cinnamon toast
directions: Butter all slices of bread.
Put on cookie sheet.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and milk till paste.
If too dry, you might have to add 2 more tablespoons of milk.
Spread on bread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with butter.
Great for big crowds.

title: microwave lemon chicken and rice
directions: Mix chicken, broth, rice, pepper, zucchini, lemon peel, lemon juice, butter, cornstarch and garlic powder in 2-quart microwave casserole.
Cover.
Microwave on High 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix melted oleo with 3 cans of soup and water.
Put rice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of soup mixture over rice.
Stir.
Salt chicken and lay on rice.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken. Bake 3 hours at 275°.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except paraffin and chocolate chips, by hand.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate or freeze until firm.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix all together.
Put in tightly covered dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° until crisp and colored.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients, adding buttermilk last.	Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage; drain well. Spray Bundt pan with nonstick spray. Separate biscuits (pull slightly to make larger circle). Place biscuits in bottom of Bundt pan overlapping (1 tube). Layer sausage, green onions and cheese. Top with second tube of biscuits, overlapping (pull apart slightly). Bake in preheated 350° oven until biscuits are done and golden brown. Turn out onto plate. Enjoy.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 2 cups hot water and 2 cups cold water. Pour into square cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve lemon jello in one cup of hot water in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add pineapple juice and cream cheese, mix with mixer until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise. Chill until thick and pour onto lime jello.
Chill until firm.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt butter and add to crushed Ritz crackers.
Pat into a 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan and freeze.
Beat softened ice cream, pudding and water until smooth.
Add ice cream mixture to crust and freeze. Add whipping cream (or Cool Whip) for topping.

title: feta fettuccine salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: mango chutney
directions: Combine drained, canned pineapple chunks, sliced dates, diced bananas, halves of maraschino cherries and shredded coconut in any desired proportions.
Pour a little pineapple syrup over all and chill well.
Serve for dessert with crisp cookies.

title: ham and cheese biscuit bake
directions: Combine Bisquick, oil and milk and beat until stiff.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine mayo and mustard. Spread over dough.
Place ham slices over dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices on top and return to oven until cheese bubbles.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased 13 x 9 pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Mix all together and bake for 50 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, melt chips and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup for later use.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream the butter with cream cheese, 1/4 cup of sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons of milk and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat at high speed until smooth and creamy.

title: frozen oreo cookie dessert
directions: Use ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble 25 Oreo cookies and line bottom of pan.
Slice 3/4 of a 1/2 gallon of fudge swirl ice cream; layer atop Oreo cookies.
Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar; spread atop ice cream.
Pour on chocolate syrup and top with 20 crumbled cookies.
Freeze and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat the eggs and add to them the milk, melted butter, dry ingredients (sifted together) and the corn (which has been cut from the cob).
By scoring the corn-on-the-cob down the center of each row with a sharp knife, then cutting off the tops, you will not get the tough husks of the kernels.
After cutting off the tops of the rows, scrape them down the back of the knife to get out the tender kernels.
Bake in a buttered dish about four inches deep in a moderate oven.
It is done when a knife comes out clean (as with custard) and brown on top.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Excellent on French fries, eggs and meat.

title: macaroni cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Let cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Let sit in fridge overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and put strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: spanish corn
directions: Mix. Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir
in
Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 1
cup
milk,	add pudding.
Let stand 3 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Blend shortening, margarine, sugar and vanilla together thoroughly.
Add milk to mixture until of spreading consistency. May be stored in refrigerator for about a week, if desired.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Stir in flour gradually, mixing well.
Mix in dates and nuts.
Press cookie dough into greased jelly roll pan (dough should be about 1/4-inch deep).
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
(Do not overcook.
Dough in oven should still be slightly puffy looking.)
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: condensed milk
directions: Place all in a blender; process until smooth.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.
This can be used in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions, garlic and peppers in a large glass bowl.
Sprinkle with and cover completely with cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours or overnight.
Drain and combine with the rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: baked onions
directions: In oblong pan, layer onions, chips, cheese, twice.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes or until done.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually and beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oil and vanilla. Fold in nuts and apple slices.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.

Use some of the flour to mix with raisins and currants (to keep them from sticking together). Add the liquids to the dry ingredients and the fruit mixture, then nuts and pour this mixture into a well-greased and floured tube pan (10-inch), Bundt pan or 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
When making for Christmas, I use colored candied sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
(Batter will be thick.)

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together.
Add pretzels. Stir and press batter into pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°. Press batter down with spatula; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; don't leave long.
Spread over pretzel mixture; seal good around the edges.
Boil 1 1/2 cups water; stir in jello.
Add frozen strawberries; mix with fork.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut up 1 chicken; place in dish. Mix first 6 ingredients in dish (9 x 13-inch pan). Salt and pepper chicken. Put on rice mixture. Pour melted margarine over chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat vegetable salad
directions: Slice cabbage; put into a large bowl.
Add carrots, peppers, cucumbers and radishes.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder and paprika.
Add to vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
This will keep for several weeks in fridge.
It is low-fat and low calorie.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into ball.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Stir milk into egg yolks and combine with sugar mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil one minute.

title: shari's apricot squares
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and coconut; combine.
Spread 3/4 of combined mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with apricot preserves.
Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: thai salmon
directions: In a well oiled skillet or stir-fry pan, heat and cook salmon over medium heat for 5 minutes on each side. While salmon is cooking, chop 2 green onions and mince 1 clove of garlic. Add green onions and garlic to pan and cook with salmon for an additional 6 to 8 minutes, turning salmon as needed to cook evenly. When salmon is done, reduce heat. Using the back of a spoon, spread Thai red curry paste on each side. Heat salmon for 1 additional minute on each side. Squeeze the juice of half a lime on salmon and transfer to plates. Garnish each plate with 1/4 lime and a whole green onion.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Remove bones from pork chops and cut into bite-size pieces. Toss with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Flour meat and brown in hot oil. Drain well and set aside. Peel potatoes and onions; slice into rounds. Layer potatoes, then onions into baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dot with margarine. Place meat on top. Mix water and milk together and pour over meat. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: pennsylvania dutch soup
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Saute sausage and drain; add potatoes and onions and boil with enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Cool soup, then add cream of celery soup mixed with 2 cups of milk.
Stir until creamy.

title: eggplant-beef casserole
directions: Peel and cook eggplant in salt water until tender; drain. Brown beef and onion.
Stir in other ingredients.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Serve over hot rice sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Separate 3 eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar; add yolks singley, beating throughly.
Stir in lemon juice. Fold in 1 cup heavy cream, stiffly beaten.
Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 the crumbs in bottom of buttered freezing tray.
Pour in lemon mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top and freeze.
Serves 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Cut up all the ingredients and add Italian dressing.
Serve cold.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix cheese(s) and onion.
Using 3 cups of mixture, fill center of tortillas.
Roll into cylinders and place seam-side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread heated chili over top and sprinkle remaining cheese/onion mixture over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: zesty crock-pot soup
directions: Slice smoked sausage into 1/4-inch "coins."
Place sausage, stewed vegetables, corn and green beans in crock-pot.
Pour juice over all.
Add water to fill.
Cook on low setting for 8 hours.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables and set aside.

title: "good-as-pizza" zucchini casserole
directions: Note:
Amount needed will depend on size casserole desired.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mash squash and add onion and butter. Add slightly beaten eggs and cream of chicken soup.
Add 1/2 can of water to soup.
Mix all together.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until done).

title: deep-fried okra
directions: Wash, trim and slice okra.
Prepare buttermilk wash:
1/2 of 1 beaten egg, water, buttermilk and salt.
Prepare seasoned mix: flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Heat vegetable oil to 350° in deep-fry pot.
Put okra slices into buttermilk wash.
Lift okra out with slotted spoon.
Place in seasoned flour and shake.
Take out and place on cake rack to sift off excess flour.
Drop into hot grease about 2 to 3 minutes and serve.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Quarter tomatoes for faster cooking. Cook until thick as desired.
Usually reduces by 1/3 to 1/2.
Can hot.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in pecans and spoon onto buttered pan.
Let chill in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate bark and dip and put on greased pan.

title: blueberry cake and frosting
directions: Bake any yellow cake mix per directions on package.
Divide into 3 layers and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chinese asparagus salad
directions: Wash and peel the asparagus with potato peeler.
Cut spears diagonally in 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Cook asparagus pieces in boiling water for 1 minute; drain and rinse under cold water to stop cooking.

title: pumpkin stack cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add to rest.
Pour 1 cup batter into 9-inch pan.
Bake 350° 15 minutes make 5 or 6 layers.
Cool completely.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: *Add enough canned broth to broth where chicken was cooked to make the 2 quarts.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°; butter pie plate.
Cook hamburg and onions; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spread in pie plate and top with green chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top with tomatoes and lettuce, if desired, and more cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer the sliced pineapple in bottom of pan.
Put a whole cherry in center of each pineapple.
Pour the crushed pineapple over the sliced pineapple.
Melt brown sugar and margarine together in microwave.
Pour over pineapple.
Mix the cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over pineapple.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken and cabbage casserole
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and coat chicken.
Reserve flour. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat and brown chicken on both sides.
Remove.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly oil muffin tins.
Sift together flour, nonfat dry milk, baking powder and salt.
Add cornmeal and mix well.
Combine eggs, water and salad oil and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins, 81 calories per muffin.
